1
00:00:01,173 --> 00:00:03,493
<i>Three weeks ago,
an invisible dome crashed down</i>

2
00:00:03,543 --> 00:00:07,651
<i>on Chester's Mill, cutting us
off from the rest of the world.</i>

3
00:00:08,481 --> 00:00:10,679
<i>The dome has tested
our limits...</i>

4
00:00:11,358 --> 00:00:12,434
Go!

5
00:00:12,475 --> 00:00:14,076
<i>...pitting us against
one another.</i>

6
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:17,305
Chester's Mill sentences
Dale Barbara to death.

7
00:00:17,344 --> 00:00:18,544
<i>...and forcing each of us</i>

8
00:00:18,583 --> 00:00:20,215
<i>to confront our own
personal demons...</i>

9
00:00:20,339 --> 00:00:22,512
<i>rage...</i>

10
00:00:22,675 --> 00:00:25,576
I need to know that you will
stand with me against <i>that!</i>

11
00:00:25,987 --> 00:00:26,585
<i>...grief...</i>

12
00:00:26,606 --> 00:00:28,695
I don't understand
who could do this to her?

13
00:00:28,926 --> 00:00:31,848
I promise you, we're going
to catch whoever did this.

14
00:00:31,895 --> 00:00:34,199
- <i>...fear...</i>
- We're trapped.

15
00:00:34,239 --> 00:00:35,834
<i>I hear we're going
to run out of water.</i>

16
00:00:39,613 --> 00:00:41,179
You killed Angie McAlister.

17
00:00:41,181 --> 00:00:43,248
<i>...shame.</i>

18
00:00:43,250 --> 00:00:45,208
I thought it would bring
the dome down.

19
00:00:45,232 --> 00:00:47,508
I would do anything
to take it back.

20
00:00:47,579 --> 00:00:50,656
<i>But we've also found love
under the dome.</i>

21
00:00:51,892 --> 00:00:56,061
<i>And we have battled to
keep our town together.</i>

22
00:00:57,163 --> 00:00:59,131
I thought the dome
was supposed to protect us.

23
00:00:59,133 --> 00:01:01,574
No, it's up to us
to protect each other.

24
00:01:01,613 --> 00:01:04,236
<i>Now we may finally have found
a way out.</i>

25
00:01:04,238 --> 00:01:05,985
<i>We hope it takes us home,</i>

26
00:01:06,032 --> 00:01:09,174
<i>but what if it takes us
to an alternate reality?</i>

27
00:01:09,976 --> 00:01:12,577
Follow me.

28
00:01:12,579 --> 00:01:14,513
We're going home.

29
00:01:14,515 --> 00:01:16,315
What do you mean, going home?

30
00:01:16,317 --> 00:01:18,350
It's time to move on.

31
00:01:28,027 --> 00:01:30,295
- Melanie.
- Barbie.

32
00:01:30,297 --> 00:01:32,030
We can't leave Julia.

33
00:01:32,732 --> 00:01:34,833
Julia said it was up to me

34
00:01:34,835 --> 00:01:36,268
to lead everybody out.

35
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:38,270
So you're just
gonna leave her here?

36
00:01:38,272 --> 00:01:40,605
She knows that
I'm coming back for her.

37
00:01:43,376 --> 00:01:46,278
Look, it's like she says.

38
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,947
Sometimes you just
got to take a leap of faith.

39
00:01:48,949 --> 00:01:50,215
Into nothingness.

40
00:01:53,287 --> 00:01:54,619
Looks better
than staying in here.

41
00:01:54,621 --> 00:01:56,755
All right, let's go.

42
00:01:56,757 --> 00:01:59,624
Everybody stick together.

43
00:02:09,135 --> 00:02:11,236
Joe!

44
00:02:12,905 --> 00:02:15,073
Norrie!

45
00:02:19,145 --> 00:02:20,512
Melanie!

46
00:02:20,514 --> 00:02:21,913
<i>We're going home.</i>

47
00:02:21,915 --> 00:02:24,082
<i>It's time to move on.</i>

48
00:02:24,084 --> 00:02:25,984
<i>Move on.</i>

49
00:02:30,289 --> 00:02:31,523
Where are we?

50
00:02:31,525 --> 00:02:33,492
- How did we get here?
- Where are we?

51
00:02:33,494 --> 00:02:35,594
Everyone here?

52
00:02:35,596 --> 00:02:37,162
I know.

53
00:02:37,164 --> 00:02:38,263
I-I have no idea.

54
00:02:38,265 --> 00:02:40,065
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

55
00:02:42,235 --> 00:02:43,435
Hey, where's Melanie?

56
00:02:43,437 --> 00:02:44,703
I don't know.

57
00:02:44,705 --> 00:02:47,506
I-I didn't see her.

58
00:02:47,508 --> 00:02:48,874
Did you hear her voice?

59
00:02:52,378 --> 00:02:54,312
What is that?

60
00:03:02,155 --> 00:03:05,090
We're outside the dome.

61
00:03:12,565 --> 00:03:14,566
Look.

62
00:03:14,568 --> 00:03:17,169
- Do you see that?
- It's changing.

63
00:03:17,171 --> 00:03:19,404
It's... it's going up.

64
00:03:19,406 --> 00:03:21,606
Where's it going?

65
00:03:21,608 --> 00:03:23,975
It's changing.

66
00:03:23,977 --> 00:03:26,678
- What is it?
- I can't tell.

67
00:03:30,783 --> 00:03:31,917
Take my hand.

68
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:49,568
My God, it's gone.

69
00:03:50,403 --> 00:03:52,003
You okay?

70
00:03:53,039 --> 00:03:55,173
Julia.

71
00:04:18,698 --> 00:04:21,666
Junior.

72
00:04:25,104 --> 00:04:27,305
Julia!

73
00:04:49,329 --> 00:04:52,731
I'm here.

74
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:55,433
Just like I promised.

75
00:04:56,769 --> 00:04:58,770
I came back for you.

76
00:05:12,104 --> 00:05:15,404
3x01/02 - <i>Move On/But I'm Not</i>

77
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:30,435
Hunter, Jawbreaker 2-3.
we're less than a klick out.

78
00:05:30,437 --> 00:05:32,637
Got you covered, boss.

79
00:05:35,441 --> 00:05:37,409
Got a drone over the location,

80
00:05:37,411 --> 00:05:39,578
no activity
in the surrounding area.

81
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:43,615
All right, on me.

82
00:05:49,922 --> 00:05:53,458
Everybody remember we're running
a standard exfil protocol.

83
00:05:53,460 --> 00:05:55,860
Intel has those hostages
guarded by a small group

84
00:05:55,862 --> 00:05:58,129
of insurgents.

85
00:06:06,872 --> 00:06:08,873
All right, that door's
our entrance point.

86
00:06:08,875 --> 00:06:10,475
That's where
they're holding 'em.

87
00:06:18,818 --> 00:06:20,885
There's no one here!

88
00:06:20,887 --> 00:06:23,154
Target's a ghost!

89
00:06:23,156 --> 00:06:25,090
Yeah, I got

90
00:06:25,092 --> 00:06:27,333
ten hostiles coming your way...
they came out of nowhere.

91
00:06:42,508 --> 00:06:44,542
You're good.
Catch your breath. Hunter,

92
00:06:44,544 --> 00:06:46,077
talk to me!

93
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,245
Rooftops are clean.

94
00:06:47,247 --> 00:06:48,747
Let me know if that changes!

95
00:07:00,761 --> 00:07:02,060
Drop it!

96
00:07:02,062 --> 00:07:03,662
Drop it! Drop it!

97
00:07:03,664 --> 00:07:05,130
Now, get down!

98
00:07:05,132 --> 00:07:06,464
- I surrender!
- Get down!

99
00:07:06,466 --> 00:07:08,933
I surrender, okay?!
I surrender!

100
00:07:08,935 --> 00:07:10,669
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

101
00:07:10,671 --> 00:07:11,703
For what?

102
00:07:21,714 --> 00:07:24,316
I got six rounds
in this magazine.

103
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:26,551
All of 'em are dummies
except for one.

104
00:07:31,258 --> 00:07:32,957
Wasn't those.

105
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:34,192
Where's the hostages?

106
00:07:34,194 --> 00:07:36,361
I don't know. I don't know.

107
00:07:37,631 --> 00:07:40,131
I'm only gonna ask you
two more times.

108
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:42,100
If you're lucky.

109
00:07:45,038 --> 00:07:46,938
Where's the hostages?

110
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:48,540
I beg you...

111
00:07:48,542 --> 00:07:50,308
Last chance.

112
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,177
Okay, okay, okay.

113
00:07:52,179 --> 00:07:54,346
I tell you.

114
00:07:54,348 --> 00:07:56,481
T... Textile factory.

115
00:07:56,483 --> 00:07:57,782
Guards.

116
00:07:57,784 --> 00:07:59,951
Five. Six-six.

117
00:08:08,595 --> 00:08:10,595
You play games?

118
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:18,002
W-Why, why?
I tell you.

119
00:08:18,771 --> 00:08:20,605
No!

120
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:28,880
You got provisions
ready to move?

121
00:08:28,882 --> 00:08:31,116
Yes, we do, sir.

122
00:08:33,753 --> 00:08:35,887
Got two more units
heading down, sir.

123
00:08:35,889 --> 00:08:37,188
Watch your step, ma'am.

124
00:08:41,261 --> 00:08:44,896
Like Steven Seagal in his
aptly-titled 1990 classic,

125
00:08:44,898 --> 00:08:46,297
you are hard to kill.

126
00:08:46,299 --> 00:08:49,067
Trust me, it ain't
from lack of trying.

127
00:08:49,069 --> 00:08:51,703
I'm glad you're back safe.
Drink later?

128
00:08:51,705 --> 00:08:54,239
No, man, I'm beat.
Another time?

129
00:08:54,241 --> 00:08:56,408
Yeah.

130
00:08:59,513 --> 00:09:02,547
I don't know how to thank you.

131
00:09:02,549 --> 00:09:05,116
Just doing what
you hired me to do.

132
00:09:05,118 --> 00:09:07,886
Yeah, well, hiring you might
be the only good decision

133
00:09:07,888 --> 00:09:10,121
I've made as operations
manager here.

134
00:09:10,123 --> 00:09:12,924
It's a tough job, trying to
make the world a safer place.

135
00:09:12,926 --> 00:09:14,993
You know, my part's easy.

136
00:09:14,995 --> 00:09:18,163
Just stop the bad guys
from making your job harder.

137
00:09:22,501 --> 00:09:24,469
Occupational hazard.

138
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:29,207
I'm gonna go get cleaned up.

139
00:10:05,478 --> 00:10:08,546
You want to talk about it?

140
00:10:08,548 --> 00:10:11,749
Talk about what?

141
00:10:11,751 --> 00:10:15,253
Whatever you had to do to save
my people, it was worth it.

142
00:10:17,591 --> 00:10:20,325
Dale.

143
00:10:20,327 --> 00:10:22,293
You don't have to
hide who you are.

144
00:10:22,295 --> 00:10:25,129
I want it all, good and bad.

145
00:10:27,099 --> 00:10:30,835
You sure about that?

146
00:10:30,837 --> 00:10:33,171
Sometimes I don't know
what side's

147
00:10:33,173 --> 00:10:35,173
gonna come out on top.

148
00:10:35,175 --> 00:10:37,242
I know.

149
00:10:38,778 --> 00:10:40,712
Who's it from?

150
00:10:40,714 --> 00:10:42,380
Joe.

151
00:10:42,382 --> 00:10:44,582
Again.

152
00:10:46,185 --> 00:10:48,853
Don't you think
that you should text him back?

153
00:10:55,227 --> 00:10:58,496
I think we should
get some sleep.

154
00:11:06,772 --> 00:11:08,840
Julia!

155
00:11:16,883 --> 00:11:18,583
I'm here.

156
00:11:18,585 --> 00:11:20,318
Just like I promised.

157
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:23,621
I came back for you.

158
00:11:27,626 --> 00:11:30,228
You were saying her name again.

159
00:11:37,269 --> 00:11:39,037
I'm sorry.

160
00:11:39,039 --> 00:11:41,573
Don't apologize.

161
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,943
It was traumatic,
what you went through.

162
00:11:44,945 --> 00:11:49,113
But you've been having this
dream for almost a year now.

163
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:53,284
Maybe it'd be a good idea
for you to go back

164
00:11:53,286 --> 00:11:56,254
to Chester's Mill
for the memorial.

165
00:11:56,256 --> 00:11:59,257
So you can move on.

166
00:12:02,861 --> 00:12:05,763
Barbie!

167
00:12:05,765 --> 00:12:07,065
Where are you?!

168
00:12:07,067 --> 00:12:09,133
Barbie's not
coming back for us.

169
00:12:09,135 --> 00:12:10,835
He will. You'll see.

170
00:12:10,837 --> 00:12:13,100
You heard that rumbling. Maybe
the tunnels caved in on them.

171
00:12:13,123 --> 00:12:14,772
- Maybe everyone's...
- Shut up.

172
00:12:14,774 --> 00:12:17,375
I don't want to hear it.

173
00:12:17,377 --> 00:12:20,144
We need to get across,
find out where they are.

174
00:12:20,146 --> 00:12:23,982
They can't be far...
they were just in front of us.

175
00:12:23,984 --> 00:12:27,085
If something's wrong,
we'll help them.

176
00:12:27,886 --> 00:12:29,921
All right.

177
00:12:29,923 --> 00:12:31,889
How?

178
00:12:35,494 --> 00:12:37,762
We can get a ladder
at the school.

179
00:12:37,764 --> 00:12:40,198
Pick up some flashlights.

180
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:51,643
What is it?

181
00:12:52,478 --> 00:12:54,646
My father.

182
00:12:56,915 --> 00:12:59,484
Jim's not the
priority right now.

183
00:12:59,486 --> 00:13:02,954
We need to get the supplies
and get back here, fast.

184
00:13:11,196 --> 00:13:13,064
Great.

185
00:13:13,066 --> 00:13:14,766
Flares?

186
00:13:14,768 --> 00:13:15,967
Just in case.

187
00:13:15,969 --> 00:13:17,702
In case we get lost at sea?

188
00:13:17,704 --> 00:13:19,671
Let's go.

189
00:13:24,076 --> 00:13:26,377
Cat get stuck up in a tree?

190
00:13:36,155 --> 00:13:38,936
Should've killed me
while you had a chance, Junior.

191
00:13:39,566 --> 00:13:40,965
Jim, you've got to let us go.

192
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,733
Yeah?
Why's that?

193
00:13:42,735 --> 00:13:44,201
You got a hair appointment?

194
00:13:45,738 --> 00:13:47,505
Them roots are looking
a little tired.

195
00:13:47,507 --> 00:13:49,740
Will you just let us go?

196
00:13:49,742 --> 00:13:51,976
If you were gonna kill us,
you would've done it already.

197
00:13:51,978 --> 00:13:53,578
Kill you?

198
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:56,847
Who said anything
about killing you?

199
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:01,686
We are the only ones left.

200
00:14:01,688 --> 00:14:04,155
I may need you.

201
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:08,526
For repopulation.

202
00:14:12,998 --> 00:14:15,166
Why'd you need the ladder?

203
00:14:20,572 --> 00:14:23,841
I said, "Why did you need
the ladder?"

204
00:14:25,377 --> 00:14:27,678
Okay.

205
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:30,815
I got nothing but time.

206
00:14:30,817 --> 00:14:34,719
It's like that old <i>Twilight
Zone</i> episode. Remember?

207
00:14:34,721 --> 00:14:36,187
With, Rocky's manager.

208
00:14:36,189 --> 00:14:37,855
The Penguin.
Wh-What's his name?

209
00:14:37,857 --> 00:14:39,223
Meredith.

210
00:14:39,225 --> 00:14:41,258
Yeah.

211
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:43,928
And he-he's all alone
after the Apocalypse,

212
00:14:43,930 --> 00:14:46,998
and all he wants to do is read.

213
00:14:48,768 --> 00:14:50,301
And then he breaks his glasses.

214
00:14:51,871 --> 00:14:53,671
I mean, talk about a tragedy.

215
00:14:53,673 --> 00:14:56,707
We need the ladder to get
across a rift in the tunnels.

216
00:14:56,709 --> 00:14:57,808
That's where everyone went.

217
00:14:57,810 --> 00:14:59,343
We need to get
across and find them.

218
00:14:59,345 --> 00:15:00,578
Find Barbie.

219
00:15:08,954 --> 00:15:10,588
You still believe, don't you?

220
00:15:10,590 --> 00:15:12,556
That the dome is good, that...

221
00:15:12,558 --> 00:15:14,492
that it's here to protect us.

222
00:15:16,161 --> 00:15:18,129
If you still believe that,
then you're even dumber

223
00:15:18,131 --> 00:15:20,197
than the bag of hair
I took you for.

224
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:25,236
The dome is here to destroy us.

225
00:15:25,238 --> 00:15:26,937
It killed them all.

226
00:15:26,939 --> 00:15:30,274
Barbie, all of them...

227
00:15:30,276 --> 00:15:32,009
- they're all dead.
- No.

228
00:15:32,011 --> 00:15:35,413
You're wrong. He's alive.

229
00:15:58,537 --> 00:16:00,738
Cut him loose.

230
00:16:03,475 --> 00:16:05,576
Go on.

231
00:16:05,578 --> 00:16:07,611
You're gonna end up dead
as the rest of 'em.

232
00:16:09,848 --> 00:16:13,150
This is my town now.
What's left of it.

233
00:16:13,152 --> 00:16:15,486
And that's the last bit
of charity you're gonna get.

234
00:16:15,488 --> 00:16:18,589
If by some miracle
you make it out alive,

235
00:16:18,591 --> 00:16:21,358
you best stay well clear of me.

236
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:25,496
'Cause if I see either
of you two again,

237
00:16:25,498 --> 00:16:28,132
I won't be so merciful
next time.

238
00:16:28,934 --> 00:16:31,102
Go on.

239
00:16:39,511 --> 00:16:40,811
Hey, Junior.

240
00:16:43,683 --> 00:16:44,582
Now we're even.

241
00:16:47,586 --> 00:16:48,919
I'm okay.

242
00:17:06,438 --> 00:17:10,274
Yeah, I don't remember it
looking this perfect.

243
00:17:10,276 --> 00:17:11,942
You okay?

244
00:17:12,844 --> 00:17:14,845
Yeah, I'm fine.

245
00:17:14,847 --> 00:17:16,946
Can we grab a bite somewhere?
I'm starving.

246
00:17:16,977 --> 00:17:18,549
Yeah, I think I know a place.

247
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:30,895
Is that Barbie?

248
00:17:30,897 --> 00:17:32,830
This place is full.

249
00:17:32,832 --> 00:17:34,665
I think
we should go somewhere else.

250
00:17:34,667 --> 00:17:38,335
Anywhere you go, there's gonna
be people who want to see you.

251
00:17:38,337 --> 00:17:41,705
You might as well face it.

252
00:17:41,707 --> 00:17:43,474
And I got to use the facilities.

253
00:17:43,476 --> 00:17:46,577
Me, too. Tiny bladder
plus a long car ride equals...

254
00:17:46,579 --> 00:17:48,813
You're not finishing
that sentence.

255
00:17:52,951 --> 00:17:54,819
Barbie!

256
00:17:54,821 --> 00:17:56,554
Hey. Joe.

257
00:17:56,556 --> 00:17:58,255
It's good to see you, bud.

258
00:17:58,257 --> 00:18:00,257
- Good to see you.
- Look at you.

259
00:18:00,259 --> 00:18:01,592
You're getting taller on me.

260
00:18:01,594 --> 00:18:02,827
It's been a year.

261
00:18:02,829 --> 00:18:06,330
Yeah. I know.

262
00:18:06,332 --> 00:18:08,732
I was worried
you weren't gonna make it back.

263
00:18:08,734 --> 00:18:10,367
I'm sorry for going...

264
00:18:10,369 --> 00:18:11,969
incommunicado. You know,

265
00:18:11,971 --> 00:18:13,804
I went overseas and then...

266
00:18:13,806 --> 00:18:15,172
I-I should've stayed in touch.

267
00:18:15,174 --> 00:18:16,574
I'm just glad you're here.

268
00:18:16,576 --> 00:18:18,375
How you holding up?

269
00:18:18,377 --> 00:18:21,345
I still think about Angie
all the time,

270
00:18:21,347 --> 00:18:22,542
especially now

271
00:18:22,573 --> 00:18:24,583
with the memorial and all, but...

272
00:18:24,584 --> 00:18:28,018
most people
lost somebody, right?

273
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:29,720
You lost two people.

274
00:18:29,722 --> 00:18:32,890
Julia and Melanie.

275
00:18:33,692 --> 00:18:35,659
So what about college?

276
00:18:35,661 --> 00:18:37,394
Did you... Have you made
any decisions?

277
00:18:37,396 --> 00:18:39,563
Yeah. Well,
I'm still waiting to hear back

278
00:18:39,565 --> 00:18:41,365
- from a couple places.
- Good.

279
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:43,734
The Great Barbini.
Welcome back, man.

280
00:18:43,736 --> 00:18:47,504
Yeah.

281
00:18:47,506 --> 00:18:49,273
Ready to jam?

282
00:18:49,275 --> 00:18:50,474
Yeah.

283
00:18:50,476 --> 00:18:52,042
We'll catch up at the memorial,
yeah?

284
00:18:52,044 --> 00:18:53,577
- Yeah. Sounds good.
- Okay.

285
00:18:53,579 --> 00:18:55,880
- It was good seeing you.
- Yeah, you, too.

286
00:19:50,784 --> 00:19:53,251
Easy, dude.
Didn't mean to spook you.

287
00:19:53,253 --> 00:19:54,819
What are you doing out here?

288
00:19:54,821 --> 00:19:56,721
After what went down
at the diner,

289
00:19:56,723 --> 00:19:58,523
you know,
I thought I'd come and find you.

290
00:19:58,525 --> 00:20:00,192
Why? What went down
at the diner?

291
00:20:00,194 --> 00:20:01,560
Aw, come on, man.

292
00:20:01,562 --> 00:20:03,128
Don't play.

293
00:20:03,130 --> 00:20:05,063
You saw Melanie, too.

294
00:20:05,065 --> 00:20:07,332
Melanie's dead.

295
00:20:07,334 --> 00:20:09,568
Is she?
In the tunnels,

296
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:12,137
she says we're going home
and then she disappears.

297
00:20:12,139 --> 00:20:13,371
Where'd she go?

298
00:20:13,373 --> 00:20:15,907
I'm not in the mood
to deal with this right now.

299
00:20:15,909 --> 00:20:17,209
You haven't been here!

300
00:20:17,211 --> 00:20:19,844
Ever since that day,
ever since the dome disappeared,

301
00:20:19,846 --> 00:20:21,813
things have been different,

302
00:20:21,815 --> 00:20:23,315
off. Like-like,
remember my asthma?

303
00:20:23,317 --> 00:20:25,650
To be honest, Ben, I remember
very little about you.

304
00:20:25,652 --> 00:20:26,785
I had asthma!

305
00:20:26,787 --> 00:20:28,887
I used to have to carry
my inhaler everywhere.

306
00:20:28,889 --> 00:20:30,121
Now asthma's gone.

307
00:20:30,123 --> 00:20:33,592
My-my uncle...
worst drunk you ever saw.

308
00:20:33,594 --> 00:20:35,460
Clean and sober, like poof.

309
00:20:35,462 --> 00:20:38,230
And beyond all that,
everyone's acting weird.

310
00:20:38,232 --> 00:20:40,432
Everyone's getting along,
all kum-bah-yah.

311
00:20:40,434 --> 00:20:44,769
Everyone's talking
about moving on and whatnot.

312
00:20:44,771 --> 00:20:46,671
You saw her, man.

313
00:20:46,673 --> 00:20:47,939
I <i>know</i> you saw her.

314
00:20:47,941 --> 00:20:49,074
Okay, and what if I did?

315
00:20:49,076 --> 00:20:50,875
Why is it just the two of us?

316
00:20:50,877 --> 00:20:53,278
I don't know!

317
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:56,081
But now I'm off all my meds,
and my head is clear

318
00:20:56,083 --> 00:20:59,117
for the first time
in, like, forever.

319
00:21:01,254 --> 00:21:02,254
Come on, man!

320
00:21:02,256 --> 00:21:03,154
What? Come on, what?

321
00:21:03,156 --> 00:21:04,456
What do you want from me?

322
00:21:04,458 --> 00:21:06,424
To admit
that you see what I see.

323
00:21:06,426 --> 00:21:08,627
Okay, what do you see, Ben?

324
00:21:10,263 --> 00:21:12,631
That none of this is real.

325
00:21:15,468 --> 00:21:17,669
Hello.

326
00:21:18,738 --> 00:21:20,739
My name is Sam,

327
00:21:20,741 --> 00:21:22,073
and I'm an alcoholic.

328
00:21:22,075 --> 00:21:25,610
I haven't had a drink
in just about a year now.

329
00:21:25,612 --> 00:21:27,212
And I want to say,
it's been a blessing

330
00:21:27,214 --> 00:21:28,480
having the support
of this group.

331
00:21:28,482 --> 00:21:30,081
Before I got here,

332
00:21:30,083 --> 00:21:32,384
I wasn't much for what
you'd call "group think."

333
00:21:32,386 --> 00:21:36,821
But the 12 steps...
got me back on the path.

334
00:21:36,823 --> 00:21:38,056
Never would have happened

335
00:21:38,058 --> 00:21:40,292
if I hadn't got sent
here a year ago.

336
00:21:40,294 --> 00:21:43,428
Strange to say it, but this
place has been good for me.

337
00:21:46,265 --> 00:21:48,266
This lawyer...

338
00:21:48,268 --> 00:21:50,735
got in touch with me recently.

339
00:21:50,737 --> 00:21:52,704
He told me there had been
some kind of screw-up

340
00:21:52,706 --> 00:21:53,972
in the chain of custody

341
00:21:53,974 --> 00:21:55,740
with the evidence
related to my case.

342
00:21:55,742 --> 00:21:57,075
He told me

343
00:21:57,077 --> 00:21:58,543
that if we appeal,

344
00:21:58,545 --> 00:22:01,012
it's possible
we could get a new trial.

345
00:22:01,014 --> 00:22:02,814
I could be a free man.

346
00:22:02,816 --> 00:22:04,516
But...

347
00:22:04,518 --> 00:22:08,386
I have to make amends
for what I've done.

348
00:22:08,388 --> 00:22:12,157
That's the step
I got to focus on.

349
00:22:12,159 --> 00:22:17,128
Making amends...
to those I've wronged.

350
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:19,064
And then...

351
00:22:19,066 --> 00:22:22,267
maybe <i>I</i> can move on.

352
00:22:23,470 --> 00:22:25,770
Is it bad that I'm
missing the pin ceremony?

353
00:22:25,772 --> 00:22:27,605
I feel like I should be here.

354
00:22:27,607 --> 00:22:29,174
And the post-game
tomorrow and...

355
00:22:29,176 --> 00:22:31,643
Nors, there's gonna
be so many post-games.

356
00:22:31,645 --> 00:22:34,312
And just so you know, if it
gets rough at this memorial,

357
00:22:34,314 --> 00:22:37,716
if you need to talk about
anything, you call me.

358
00:22:37,718 --> 00:22:38,983
I'm here for you.

359
00:22:40,954 --> 00:22:43,088
All right, little sis.

360
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:44,989
Are you ready for your pin?

361
00:22:50,096 --> 00:22:51,663
You're one of us now.

362
00:22:55,102 --> 00:22:57,102
You got your pin!

363
00:22:57,104 --> 00:22:59,137
How does it feel?

364
00:22:59,139 --> 00:23:01,005
It feels great.

365
00:23:01,007 --> 00:23:03,375
I think it's just
what you needed.

366
00:23:03,377 --> 00:23:06,978
Finding your group
in college is important.

367
00:23:06,980 --> 00:23:11,216
To be part of something
that is bigger than yourself.

368
00:23:11,218 --> 00:23:13,251
Not to mention,

369
00:23:13,253 --> 00:23:15,720
you don't seem
so angry anymore.

370
00:23:15,722 --> 00:23:17,222
What is it?

371
00:23:17,224 --> 00:23:19,557
Joe hasn't been
texting me back.

372
00:23:19,559 --> 00:23:23,561
It'll be good for you
to see him... as friends.

373
00:23:23,563 --> 00:23:27,232
Are you questioning
your decision?

374
00:23:27,234 --> 00:23:29,200
To break things off? No.

375
00:23:29,202 --> 00:23:32,837
But I just wish he wasn't
being so high school about it.

376
00:23:32,839 --> 00:23:37,409
And I wish he could see that
it's not so scary, moving on.

377
00:23:38,577 --> 00:23:40,245
That's why it's important

378
00:23:40,247 --> 00:23:42,614
for you to go to the memorial.

379
00:23:42,616 --> 00:23:44,983
To pay respects
to your mother, of course,

380
00:23:44,985 --> 00:23:46,918
but also to show Joe,

381
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:49,854
there's a way forward,
out of grief.

382
00:23:49,856 --> 00:23:51,990
You'll talk to him.

383
00:24:08,140 --> 00:24:10,175
What are you doing in my room?

384
00:24:10,177 --> 00:24:11,843
Your mother let me in.

385
00:24:11,845 --> 00:24:13,812
You've blown off
our last few therapy sessions.

386
00:24:13,814 --> 00:24:14,913
So what?

387
00:24:14,915 --> 00:24:17,282
What do I need therapy for
anyway?

388
00:24:17,284 --> 00:24:19,751
I'm making straight A's,
I'm working hard.

389
00:24:19,753 --> 00:24:22,287
I know you are,
which makes me wonder

390
00:24:22,289 --> 00:24:25,390
why you'd want to throw
all that hard work away.

391
00:24:25,392 --> 00:24:27,125
Acceptance letter to Cal Tech.

392
00:24:27,127 --> 00:24:30,195
That's the best engineering
program in the country.

393
00:24:30,197 --> 00:24:32,897
Why haven't you responded yet?

394
00:24:32,899 --> 00:24:34,799
I'm going to.

395
00:24:34,801 --> 00:24:36,501
I-I just...

396
00:24:36,503 --> 00:24:38,703
I haven't gotten around to it.

397
00:24:50,416 --> 00:24:52,350
Tell me the truth.

398
00:24:52,352 --> 00:24:54,519
Are you reconsidering the plan?

399
00:24:54,521 --> 00:24:56,521
No. No, I-I... I just...

400
00:24:58,124 --> 00:25:00,458
I've been wondering
if this is the best time

401
00:25:00,460 --> 00:25:01,593
to leave Chester's Mill.

402
00:25:01,595 --> 00:25:03,761
My parents are still dealing...

403
00:25:03,763 --> 00:25:06,331
Your parents don't
need you, Joe.

404
00:25:11,570 --> 00:25:13,605
No matter what you do,

405
00:25:13,607 --> 00:25:16,040
staying in Chester's Mill

406
00:25:16,042 --> 00:25:18,710
won't keep her alive.

407
00:25:21,347 --> 00:25:23,348
It's up to you, of course,

408
00:25:23,350 --> 00:25:25,917
but I think it's important

409
00:25:25,919 --> 00:25:29,187
that you speak at the
memorial about Angie.

410
00:25:29,189 --> 00:25:32,824
All the feelings that you've
repressed since her murder.

411
00:25:32,826 --> 00:25:35,527
The sorrow, the guilt.

412
00:25:35,529 --> 00:25:38,129
It might help give you
the closure that you need

413
00:25:38,131 --> 00:25:40,932
and allow you to
take the next step.

414
00:25:42,801 --> 00:25:46,204
Your sister wouldn't have wanted
you to hold yourself back, Joe.

415
00:25:46,206 --> 00:25:48,373
She would have wanted
you to move on.

416
00:25:52,778 --> 00:25:54,779
Please, just think about it?

417
00:25:54,781 --> 00:25:57,482
I'll see you at the memorial.

418
00:26:25,878 --> 00:26:27,011
Long way down.

419
00:26:27,013 --> 00:26:29,180
"Long" doesn't quite cover it.

420
00:26:29,182 --> 00:26:31,115
I'll go first.

421
00:26:36,356 --> 00:26:38,790
It's Big Jim's, just in case.

422
00:26:38,792 --> 00:26:41,759
In case I get challenged
to a knife fight?

423
00:27:00,547 --> 00:27:02,547
It bit me!

424
00:27:02,549 --> 00:27:04,816
Keep going.

425
00:27:21,468 --> 00:27:23,835
Julia?

426
00:28:19,603 --> 00:28:21,938
Junior?

427
00:28:28,345 --> 00:28:30,513
Junior?

428
00:28:42,059 --> 00:28:44,027
Did you speak with him?

429
00:28:44,029 --> 00:28:46,763
How are you, Sam?

430
00:28:46,765 --> 00:28:48,765
I'm well.

431
00:28:48,767 --> 00:28:50,733
As well as can be expected.

432
00:28:50,735 --> 00:28:52,669
Day by day, you know?

433
00:28:52,671 --> 00:28:55,371
I do. That's good to hear.

434
00:28:58,042 --> 00:28:59,976
I haven't spoken
to Joe about it,

435
00:28:59,978 --> 00:29:01,878
and I know that disappoints you.

436
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:05,548
But the dome coming
down, your trial,

437
00:29:05,550 --> 00:29:08,952
all the emotions that Joe has
kept such a tight lid on...

438
00:29:08,954 --> 00:29:12,522
it's understandable why
he's expressing them now.

439
00:29:12,524 --> 00:29:14,958
Try to be patient?

440
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:17,193
What are you thinking?

441
00:29:17,195 --> 00:29:18,428
That I really want a drink.

442
00:29:18,430 --> 00:29:19,963
Well, it's good
there's not a bar around.

443
00:29:19,965 --> 00:29:21,564
You think
there's no options in here?

444
00:29:22,968 --> 00:29:24,834
You'd be amazed by the options.

445
00:29:26,871 --> 00:29:29,138
You don't need a drink, Sam.

446
00:29:29,140 --> 00:29:32,442
What you need... is
to forgive yourself.

447
00:29:32,444 --> 00:29:35,044
I don't know if I can do that.

448
00:29:35,046 --> 00:29:36,913
Not if Joe can't forgive me.

449
00:29:36,915 --> 00:29:39,482
And what if he doesn't?

450
00:29:39,484 --> 00:29:41,484
You did a terrible thing, Sam,

451
00:29:41,486 --> 00:29:44,587
but that one terrible thing
doesn't have to define you.

452
00:29:44,589 --> 00:29:46,789
The lawyer that
I sent to you...

453
00:29:46,791 --> 00:29:49,492
he told me that you wouldn't
appeal your case. Why?

454
00:29:49,494 --> 00:29:51,094
Because I deserve to be here.

455
00:29:51,096 --> 00:29:53,196
You were an EMT before, yes?

456
00:29:53,198 --> 00:29:57,066
Well, from my experience, no one
goes into that line of work

457
00:29:57,068 --> 00:29:59,135
who doesn't have a deep desire

458
00:29:59,137 --> 00:30:02,305
to help people, heal people.

459
00:30:03,207 --> 00:30:05,241
If you appealed, and
you were released,

460
00:30:05,243 --> 00:30:08,244
think of all the people
that you could affect.

461
00:30:11,282 --> 00:30:12,982
You know the memorial's today.

462
00:30:12,984 --> 00:30:14,417
Of course.

463
00:30:14,419 --> 00:30:15,885
If you'd spoken to the lawyer,

464
00:30:15,887 --> 00:30:18,054
he might have been able
to arrange a short furlough.

465
00:30:18,056 --> 00:30:20,690
I'd never be welcome there.

466
00:30:22,626 --> 00:30:24,594
Maybe you could write something.

467
00:30:24,596 --> 00:30:26,596
Something I could read later.

468
00:30:26,598 --> 00:30:29,032
Then at least you'd be a <i>part</i>
of the memorial.

469
00:30:29,034 --> 00:30:30,934
Perhaps it might
help you make amends.

470
00:30:30,936 --> 00:30:33,169
I need to speak to Joe.

471
00:30:33,171 --> 00:30:34,871
And you will.

472
00:30:34,873 --> 00:30:37,707
But Joe has to be ready
to hear you, and...

473
00:30:37,709 --> 00:30:39,943
I don't think he is just yet.

474
00:30:41,111 --> 00:30:43,513
I'm ready when you are.

475
00:31:30,861 --> 00:31:33,062
Glad we came?

476
00:31:38,469 --> 00:31:40,703
Yeah, I am.

477
00:31:40,705 --> 00:31:42,772
It was a good idea.

478
00:31:42,774 --> 00:31:45,141
Excuse me.
Are you Dale Barbara?

479
00:31:45,143 --> 00:31:46,576
Yes, ma'am.

480
00:31:46,578 --> 00:31:47,744
Christine Price.

481
00:31:47,746 --> 00:31:50,613
FEMA sent me here after
the dome came down.

482
00:31:50,615 --> 00:31:53,182
For what?

483
00:31:53,184 --> 00:31:54,651
I'm a trauma specialist.

484
00:31:54,653 --> 00:31:56,686
I help communities
recover after,

485
00:31:56,688 --> 00:31:59,255
shall we say, stressful events.

486
00:31:59,257 --> 00:32:01,791
I tried to reach out
to you after I arrived,

487
00:32:01,793 --> 00:32:04,093
but it seemed
you'd already moved on.

488
00:32:04,095 --> 00:32:07,530
I guess I didn't see much
of a reason to stick around.

489
00:32:07,532 --> 00:32:09,465
Well...

490
00:32:09,467 --> 00:32:12,168
if you ever feel like talking,
I'm at your disposal.

491
00:32:12,170 --> 00:32:14,771
I'm Eva. I'm here with him.

492
00:32:14,773 --> 00:32:16,706
- Eva. Christine.
- I was here

493
00:32:16,708 --> 00:32:18,207
for the stressful events.

494
00:32:18,209 --> 00:32:20,176
Does that mean you're
at my disposal, too?

495
00:32:22,312 --> 00:32:24,480
Anytime.

496
00:32:25,849 --> 00:32:27,884
Almost forgot.

497
00:32:27,886 --> 00:32:30,286
Would you care
to say a few words today

498
00:32:30,288 --> 00:32:31,854
about Julia Shumway?

499
00:32:31,856 --> 00:32:35,625
Y-You know,
I'm not really much for...

500
00:32:35,627 --> 00:32:37,393
for public speaking.

501
00:32:38,228 --> 00:32:40,430
All right.

502
00:33:05,622 --> 00:33:08,224
I wish you wouldn't do that.

503
00:33:22,439 --> 00:33:25,241
Joe.

504
00:33:27,077 --> 00:33:29,279
I've been trying to
get in touch with you.

505
00:33:29,310 --> 00:33:30,179
Why?

506
00:33:30,181 --> 00:33:32,615
I thought you were all about
getting some distance

507
00:33:32,617 --> 00:33:34,050
or whatever.

508
00:33:34,052 --> 00:33:37,120
That doesn't mean
I don't still care about you.

509
00:33:38,455 --> 00:33:40,656
They asked me
to talk about Angie.

510
00:33:40,658 --> 00:33:41,924
Are you going to?

511
00:33:41,926 --> 00:33:43,993
I don't know.

512
00:33:43,995 --> 00:33:46,162
I don't know what to say...

513
00:33:46,164 --> 00:33:48,998
except that
she was a good sister.

514
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,000
She could be tough,

515
00:33:51,002 --> 00:33:53,236
but...

516
00:33:53,238 --> 00:33:55,438
she looked out for me.

517
00:33:56,974 --> 00:34:00,643
I just wish
I could have looked out for her.

518
00:34:08,585 --> 00:34:09,852
Jump, Junior!

519
00:34:09,854 --> 00:34:11,254
I can't!

520
00:34:11,256 --> 00:34:13,256
Yes, you can!
Stop being a fraidy cat!

521
00:34:13,258 --> 00:34:15,358
Be a man!

522
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:17,527
Be a man.

523
00:34:17,529 --> 00:34:19,362
Dad, I want to get down!

524
00:34:19,364 --> 00:34:23,032
You don't jump,
you don't come home tonight!

525
00:34:23,034 --> 00:34:25,968
Dad, where are you going?

526
00:34:25,970 --> 00:34:27,403
Come back!

527
00:34:27,405 --> 00:34:29,105
Don't leave me here!

528
00:34:30,808 --> 00:34:34,610
Nothing good on television
these days, anyway.

529
00:34:38,783 --> 00:34:41,083
Junior! Junior!

530
00:34:52,530 --> 00:34:54,530
Over here, you bastards.

531
00:35:07,929 --> 00:35:09,797
Junior?

532
00:35:23,678 --> 00:35:25,813
A year ago,
the people of this town

533
00:35:25,815 --> 00:35:27,782
were delivered from the dome.

534
00:35:27,784 --> 00:35:32,787
But some of you, many of you,
also suffered a great loss.

535
00:35:32,789 --> 00:35:34,688
Of friends.

536
00:35:34,690 --> 00:35:36,524
Of family.

537
00:35:36,526 --> 00:35:38,192
After a shared tragedy,

538
00:35:38,194 --> 00:35:40,661
there's nothing
that provides more consolation

539
00:35:40,663 --> 00:35:42,263
than a sense of community.

540
00:35:42,265 --> 00:35:45,366
Those lives
will never be forgotten,

541
00:35:45,368 --> 00:35:48,869
and their memory will be
preserved in an eternal flame

542
00:35:48,871 --> 00:35:51,472
here at the monument.

543
00:35:51,474 --> 00:35:52,873
A memorial is

544
00:35:52,875 --> 00:35:54,575
about moving forward,

545
00:35:54,577 --> 00:35:56,610
moving on, together.

546
00:35:56,612 --> 00:35:58,746
To that effect,
I'd like to read

547
00:35:58,748 --> 00:36:02,583
a brief epigraph from someone
who couldn't be here today.

548
00:36:04,052 --> 00:36:05,986
"Make a way in the wilderness,

549
00:36:05,988 --> 00:36:07,955
"and do not remember
the former things

550
00:36:07,957 --> 00:36:09,690
"or consider the things of old.

551
00:36:09,692 --> 00:36:11,926
"For when you walk
through fire,

552
00:36:11,928 --> 00:36:14,028
"you shall not be burned,

553
00:36:14,030 --> 00:36:17,331
and the flame
shall not consume you."

554
00:36:19,034 --> 00:36:22,937
Is there anyone
who would care to speak first?

555
00:36:31,513 --> 00:36:35,449
I wasn't planning
on saying anything today,

556
00:36:35,451 --> 00:36:38,118
but a lot of you
knew my sister,

557
00:36:38,120 --> 00:36:39,620
Angie McAlister.

558
00:36:39,622 --> 00:36:42,957
Some of you knew her
as a waitress at the Sweetbriar.

559
00:36:42,959 --> 00:36:47,461
Some of you knew her as
a volunteer down at the clinic.

560
00:36:47,463 --> 00:36:49,496
Me...

561
00:36:49,498 --> 00:36:52,633
I just always knew her.

562
00:36:53,668 --> 00:36:57,671
And she was so full
of life, you know?

563
00:37:00,476 --> 00:37:03,077
It's hard to accept that...

564
00:37:03,079 --> 00:37:05,012
that she's gone,

565
00:37:05,014 --> 00:37:08,015
to say good-bye,

566
00:37:08,017 --> 00:37:12,186
to lose someone
that you love the most.

567
00:37:14,322 --> 00:37:16,857
And it's hard to move on, but...

568
00:37:16,859 --> 00:37:20,327
I'm trying.

569
00:37:21,463 --> 00:37:24,131
I don't know what to...

570
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,233
Joe here,

571
00:37:26,235 --> 00:37:28,969
he was one of the first people
that I met

572
00:37:28,971 --> 00:37:30,571
when I came to Chester's Mill.

573
00:37:30,573 --> 00:37:33,507
I was a stranger to
him, to all of you.

574
00:37:33,509 --> 00:37:35,876
He made me feel

575
00:37:35,878 --> 00:37:37,678
like I belonged.

576
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:41,081
First time I felt that
in a long time.

577
00:37:41,950 --> 00:37:43,083
The people of Chester's Mill

578
00:37:43,085 --> 00:37:46,120
opened their hearts to me.

579
00:37:46,122 --> 00:37:50,658
And that, I think,
allowed me to open mine.

580
00:37:52,093 --> 00:37:56,330
Especially to a woman
named Julia Shumway.

581
00:37:56,332 --> 00:37:58,299
<i>What can I say about Julia?</i>

582
00:37:58,301 --> 00:38:00,734
<i>She was the bravest woman
I ever met.</i>

583
00:38:00,736 --> 00:38:03,070
<i>She was endlessly curious.</i>

584
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,972
<i>She was, quite possibly,</i>

585
00:38:04,974 --> 00:38:07,641
<i>the most stubborn individual
to walk this earth</i>

586
00:38:07,643 --> 00:38:11,345
<i>in its four billion
or so years.</i>

587
00:38:11,347 --> 00:38:13,414
She was loyal.

588
00:38:13,416 --> 00:38:15,616
She always had your back.

589
00:38:15,618 --> 00:38:17,918
Always rooting
for the underdog.

590
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,386
And she couldn't help it.

591
00:38:19,388 --> 00:38:21,789
She just... She never
lost her faith

592
00:38:21,791 --> 00:38:24,625
in the basic goodness
of humanity.

593
00:38:24,627 --> 00:38:26,427
Like Christine here said,

594
00:38:26,429 --> 00:38:28,329
even though Julia

595
00:38:28,331 --> 00:38:31,432
and-and many of your own
loved ones are gone...

596
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:34,635
they'll never be forgotten.

597
00:38:34,637 --> 00:38:37,035
I think it's important to learn

598
00:38:37,066 --> 00:38:38,472
that we can both remember

599
00:38:38,474 --> 00:38:39,907
and move on

600
00:38:39,909 --> 00:38:41,375
at the same time.

601
00:38:42,378 --> 00:38:43,978
Ben!

602
00:38:43,980 --> 00:38:45,980
- Somebody help him!
- Ben!

603
00:38:45,982 --> 00:38:48,182
I'll call 911.

604
00:38:48,184 --> 00:38:49,650
- Is he okay?
- Is there a doctor here?

605
00:38:49,652 --> 00:38:50,985
Someone call an ambulance.

606
00:38:50,987 --> 00:38:52,119
Where's his inhaler?

607
00:38:52,121 --> 00:38:53,487
Why doesn't he have it?

608
00:38:53,489 --> 00:38:54,388
He's choking on something.

609
00:38:54,390 --> 00:38:55,990
Ben! Come on, man!

610
00:38:58,159 --> 00:39:00,427
Breathe. Breathe. Breathe.

611
00:39:00,429 --> 00:39:02,463
It's time to move on.

612
00:39:02,465 --> 00:39:04,598
Come on, Ben.

613
00:39:23,284 --> 00:39:25,452
I'm sorry.

614
00:39:47,609 --> 00:39:50,010
My God.

615
00:40:23,912 --> 00:40:25,779
Joe.

616
00:40:46,501 --> 00:40:49,236
Norrie.

617
00:41:17,933 --> 00:41:20,635
Junior?

618
00:41:22,471 --> 00:41:24,372
Junior?

619
00:41:24,374 --> 00:41:26,541
Wake up.

620
00:41:29,044 --> 00:41:30,411
Melanie.

621
00:41:31,580 --> 00:41:33,181
But how are you...?

622
00:41:33,183 --> 00:41:34,716
It's all right.

623
00:41:34,718 --> 00:41:36,884
You're safe now.

624
00:41:42,291 --> 00:41:43,827
When the ground
opened up and took you,

625
00:41:43,851 --> 00:41:45,460
I thought I'd never
see you again.

626
00:41:45,462 --> 00:41:47,361
I was brought here.

627
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,135
What is this place?

628
00:41:54,137 --> 00:41:55,403
I can explain everything,

629
00:41:55,405 --> 00:41:58,573
but first...
I have to show you something.

630
00:42:34,076 --> 00:42:36,244
I don't understand.

631
00:42:36,246 --> 00:42:38,479
What did you want to show me?

632
00:42:38,481 --> 00:42:39,714
There's nothing here.

633
00:42:39,716 --> 00:42:40,915
We're here.

634
00:42:40,917 --> 00:42:43,050
That's all that matters.

635
00:42:43,052 --> 00:42:45,253
You're afraid.

636
00:42:45,255 --> 00:42:48,956
But I need you to trust me.

637
00:42:48,958 --> 00:42:50,658
It'll be okay.

638
00:42:50,660 --> 00:42:53,661
No, no. I have to,
I have to get back to Julia.

639
00:42:54,797 --> 00:42:57,732
I could always feel your pain.

640
00:42:59,201 --> 00:43:01,369
Let me take it all away.

641
00:43:19,421 --> 00:43:22,056
- Melanie!
<i>- I'm over here.</i>

642
00:43:22,058 --> 00:43:23,491
<i>Don't be afraid.</i>

643
00:43:23,493 --> 00:43:24,859
Melanie!

644
00:43:24,861 --> 00:43:25,813
<i>You're not alone.</i>

645
00:43:25,852 --> 00:43:28,209
<i>It's time to move on
like the others.</i>

646
00:43:28,241 --> 00:43:29,197
Where are you?!

647
00:43:29,199 --> 00:43:31,265
I'm right here, baby.

648
00:43:33,969 --> 00:43:35,069
What's happening?!

649
00:43:36,606 --> 00:43:39,073
Melanie!

650
00:43:39,075 --> 00:43:40,174
Soon, this will

651
00:43:40,176 --> 00:43:41,843
all be over,
once you and your friends

652
00:43:41,845 --> 00:43:43,911
become who we need you to be.

653
00:43:43,913 --> 00:43:45,546
It's the only way
we'll survive.

654
00:43:45,548 --> 00:43:48,115
Melanie... please don't do this.

655
00:43:48,117 --> 00:43:51,552
But first we have to fix you.

656
00:43:51,554 --> 00:43:53,754
Melanie! Melanie!

657
00:44:26,622 --> 00:44:28,322
Julia, stop!

658
00:44:28,324 --> 00:44:30,858
Melanie?

659
00:44:30,860 --> 00:44:34,195
My God, you're alive.

660
00:44:38,433 --> 00:44:40,268
What happened to you?

661
00:44:40,270 --> 00:44:42,303
I'm not sure.

662
00:44:42,305 --> 00:44:44,338
It's all a blur.

663
00:44:44,340 --> 00:44:46,307
It's okay.

664
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:48,209
It's okay.
You're here now.

665
00:44:48,211 --> 00:44:49,944
That's all that matters.

666
00:44:49,946 --> 00:44:53,347
I need you to help me
free Barbie.

667
00:44:53,349 --> 00:44:55,750
And the rest of them.

668
00:44:55,752 --> 00:44:57,919
You can't.

669
00:44:57,921 --> 00:45:00,021
You can't help any of them.

670
00:45:00,023 --> 00:45:01,322
Well, I have to try.

671
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:03,190
No, you don't understand.

672
00:45:03,192 --> 00:45:06,727
If you free him, you'll
end up like all the others.

673
00:45:06,729 --> 00:45:07,795
Like Junior.

674
00:45:07,797 --> 00:45:09,297
Junior?

675
00:45:09,299 --> 00:45:11,232
He was just with me.

676
00:45:11,234 --> 00:45:12,474
We were in the
tunnels together.

677
00:45:12,481 --> 00:45:13,701
We got separated.

678
00:45:13,703 --> 00:45:15,903
I'll show you.

679
00:45:19,174 --> 00:45:20,541
After I was

680
00:45:20,543 --> 00:45:24,111
pulled underground,
I was unconscious.

681
00:45:24,113 --> 00:45:27,515
Trapped in one of these
until he cut me free.

682
00:45:27,517 --> 00:45:28,582
And then one of those, it...

683
00:45:28,584 --> 00:45:31,085
it wrapped around his legs,
his body.

684
00:45:31,087 --> 00:45:33,120
I couldn't save him.

685
00:45:33,122 --> 00:45:35,823
Please, Julia, we should go.

686
00:45:35,825 --> 00:45:38,392
No.

687
00:45:38,394 --> 00:45:39,927
No, I'm not giving up...

688
00:45:39,929 --> 00:45:42,663
on Barbie;
on our friends!

689
00:45:44,534 --> 00:45:46,634
Julia, your leg.

690
00:45:46,636 --> 00:45:47,768
You're hurt,

691
00:45:47,770 --> 00:45:49,370
exhausted.
Let me help.

692
00:45:49,372 --> 00:45:52,006
Look.

693
00:45:52,008 --> 00:45:55,943
These... things...

694
00:45:55,945 --> 00:45:58,245
connecting all the cocoons...

695
00:46:01,616 --> 00:46:04,385
...and they're all coming
from up there.

696
00:46:07,756 --> 00:46:09,390
Julia, I'm scared!

697
00:46:09,392 --> 00:46:12,393
This cocoon, it's... different.

698
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:15,529
It's larger.

699
00:46:15,531 --> 00:46:16,964
I can't see who's inside.

700
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:20,468
The egg.

701
00:46:20,470 --> 00:46:23,204
Dome.

702
00:46:23,206 --> 00:46:25,806
These cocoons.

703
00:46:25,808 --> 00:46:27,975
There's got to be a connection.

704
00:46:30,645 --> 00:46:32,346
What if the egg is like...

705
00:46:32,348 --> 00:46:34,548
a key...

706
00:46:34,550 --> 00:46:36,183
to unlock the cocoons?

707
00:46:36,185 --> 00:46:39,224
Your father didn't bring
the egg back from Zenith.

708
00:46:39,255 --> 00:46:41,889
But you told me he was
on his way to Chester's Mill.

709
00:46:41,891 --> 00:46:44,025
We need the egg!

710
00:46:44,027 --> 00:46:46,093
How can you be so sure?

711
00:46:46,095 --> 00:46:47,428
You saw what happened to me

712
00:46:47,430 --> 00:46:48,996
when it was taken
from Chester's Mill.

713
00:46:48,998 --> 00:46:51,332
I'm... I'm connected to it

714
00:46:51,334 --> 00:46:52,833
somehow.

715
00:46:52,835 --> 00:46:54,802
I almost died.
I can't explain it.

716
00:46:54,804 --> 00:46:56,404
I just know

717
00:46:56,406 --> 00:46:59,206
we have to have the egg.

718
00:47:00,475 --> 00:47:04,045
We need to find a way to
get a message to my father.

719
00:47:05,247 --> 00:47:07,648
What's wrong?

720
00:47:07,650 --> 00:47:10,217
There's just one problem.

721
00:47:22,899 --> 00:47:24,432
Get out of here!

722
00:47:24,434 --> 00:47:25,566
Go on! Get!

723
00:47:25,568 --> 00:47:27,401
Yeah, that's right!

724
00:47:27,403 --> 00:47:29,470
This is mine!
This is all mine!

725
00:47:29,472 --> 00:47:31,005
You better run.

726
00:47:31,007 --> 00:47:34,008
You hear me?

727
00:47:38,947 --> 00:47:40,414
Boss!

728
00:47:40,416 --> 00:47:41,515
Is there a problem?

729
00:47:41,517 --> 00:47:43,684
After the memorial
last night, I was

730
00:47:43,686 --> 00:47:46,353
pretty messed up,
so I found some...

731
00:47:46,355 --> 00:47:49,590
comfort?

732
00:47:49,592 --> 00:47:51,992
She needs to go now.

733
00:47:51,994 --> 00:47:53,594
Roger that.

734
00:47:53,596 --> 00:47:56,017
Change of plans.

735
00:47:56,049 --> 00:47:57,665
- It's a... work thing.
- But...

736
00:47:57,667 --> 00:47:58,999
I'll call.

737
00:48:03,839 --> 00:48:06,574
Hi.

738
00:48:06,576 --> 00:48:07,775
Yeah.

739
00:48:07,777 --> 00:48:10,344
He'll call.

740
00:48:10,346 --> 00:48:13,347
Can you unlock this?

741
00:48:13,349 --> 00:48:15,282
You insult me.

742
00:48:15,284 --> 00:48:17,318
From the look of that vein
in your forehead,

743
00:48:17,320 --> 00:48:18,352
whatever's on here's
got to be...

744
00:48:18,354 --> 00:48:19,720
Yeah, it's important.

745
00:48:22,525 --> 00:48:24,725
Yeah, and unlocked.

746
00:48:24,727 --> 00:48:26,994
Okay, so this video right here,

747
00:48:26,996 --> 00:48:29,029
this was taken yesterday
right before Ben died.

748
00:48:29,031 --> 00:48:32,533
You lifted the
dead kid's phone?

749
00:48:32,535 --> 00:48:35,603
Not judging.

750
00:48:35,605 --> 00:48:37,805
Chester's Mill cop.

751
00:48:37,807 --> 00:48:39,373
Chester's Mill groundkeeper.

752
00:48:39,375 --> 00:48:41,075
Chester's Mill delivery guy.

753
00:48:41,077 --> 00:48:43,010
Different hair,
different clothes.

754
00:48:43,012 --> 00:48:44,645
Moustache, no moustache.

755
00:48:44,647 --> 00:48:47,214
But here's where it gets weird.

756
00:48:47,216 --> 00:48:48,682
They're all the same
freaking face.

757
00:48:48,684 --> 00:48:50,582
Barbie, I'm telling you
they're all the same dude.

758
00:48:50,605 --> 00:48:52,949
Whatever's going down
in Chester's Mill,

759
00:48:52,972 --> 00:48:55,189
here's proof that it ain't real.

760
00:48:55,191 --> 00:48:57,591
What did he mean "not real"?

761
00:48:57,593 --> 00:48:59,660
Plug this in.

762
00:48:59,662 --> 00:49:00,694
I want you to play it again.

763
00:49:00,696 --> 00:49:02,129
Punch in on their faces.

764
00:49:02,131 --> 00:49:04,965
No prob.

765
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:11,005
Chest... Mill...

766
00:49:11,007 --> 00:49:12,859
No, no, no.

767
00:49:12,890 --> 00:49:14,308
What the hell? What's happening?

768
00:49:14,310 --> 00:49:15,643
I-I-I don't know.

769
00:49:15,645 --> 00:49:17,444
The file's, like,
corrupted or something.

770
00:49:17,446 --> 00:49:19,013
- Okay, so then fix it.
- I'm trying! I...

771
00:49:19,015 --> 00:49:20,814
This makes no sen... I...

772
00:49:20,816 --> 00:49:23,003
Okay, I need you to do whatever
it takes to retrieve that file.

773
00:49:23,034 --> 00:49:25,786
Do you understand me?

774
00:49:25,788 --> 00:49:27,087
Yeah.

775
00:49:27,089 --> 00:49:29,390
Meet me at the
'Briar in an hour.

776
00:49:30,525 --> 00:49:33,160
Ben was such a good friend.

777
00:49:33,162 --> 00:49:35,129
I can't believe he's dead.

778
00:49:35,131 --> 00:49:37,531
Chester's Mill strikes again.

779
00:49:39,335 --> 00:49:41,535
It doesn't make any sense.

780
00:49:47,742 --> 00:49:48,709
What?

781
00:49:48,711 --> 00:49:50,077
Go to college

782
00:49:50,079 --> 00:49:51,679
and gain, like, 15 pounds.

783
00:49:51,681 --> 00:49:53,314
It helps keep the weight off.

784
00:49:53,316 --> 00:49:56,951
You're so gonna love it there.

785
00:49:56,953 --> 00:49:59,053
Who says I'm even going?

786
00:50:00,856 --> 00:50:03,724
It's like you're trapped under a
dome and you can't even see it.

787
00:50:03,726 --> 00:50:05,359
Joe,

788
00:50:05,361 --> 00:50:06,927
this isn't what Angie
would've wanted.

789
00:50:06,929 --> 00:50:08,429
She was my sister...

790
00:50:08,431 --> 00:50:10,264
Yeah, and she's dead!

791
00:50:10,266 --> 00:50:12,233
Just like my mom.

792
00:50:12,235 --> 00:50:14,702
And it sucks and it's unfair.

793
00:50:14,704 --> 00:50:17,104
But that doesn't mean
you stop living.

794
00:50:18,540 --> 00:50:21,575
Leaving Chester's Mill
is the best thing I ever did.

795
00:50:21,577 --> 00:50:24,445
It allowed me to heal
and to meet new people.

796
00:50:24,447 --> 00:50:28,115
I feel like a different person
and I want that for you, too.

797
00:50:28,117 --> 00:50:30,150
You're different, all right.

798
00:50:30,952 --> 00:50:32,219
The clothes, the hair.

799
00:50:32,221 --> 00:50:34,421
A sorority? Seriously?

800
00:50:34,423 --> 00:50:37,191
It's nice to be a part of
something bigger than yourself.

801
00:50:37,993 --> 00:50:39,660
To belong.

802
00:50:39,662 --> 00:50:42,463
Is that why you haven't been
back here in over a year?

803
00:50:42,465 --> 00:50:43,831
You're too busy belonging?

804
00:50:43,833 --> 00:50:45,299
We decided that
we would take a break

805
00:50:45,301 --> 00:50:46,800
until you graduate, Joe.

806
00:50:46,802 --> 00:50:49,003
It was great catching up
with you, Norrie.

807
00:50:50,672 --> 00:50:53,073
Joe.

808
00:50:58,213 --> 00:50:59,580
Damn it.

809
00:51:07,355 --> 00:51:09,423
Eva?

810
00:51:10,258 --> 00:51:11,558
Check-out's at noon, slowpoke.

811
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:13,127
You haven't even packed.

812
00:51:14,229 --> 00:51:16,597
Yeah, I wanted to talk
to you about that.

813
00:51:16,599 --> 00:51:18,565
Everything okay?

814
00:51:18,567 --> 00:51:21,101
You think it'd be all right
if we stayed another day?

815
00:51:21,103 --> 00:51:23,270
With everything
that happened with Ben

816
00:51:23,272 --> 00:51:25,072
and the memorial,

817
00:51:25,074 --> 00:51:26,573
I think we should stick around.

818
00:51:26,575 --> 00:51:28,008
Everyone was pretty shaken up.

819
00:51:28,010 --> 00:51:29,476
Yeah, you were
pretty shaken up.

820
00:51:29,478 --> 00:51:31,178
You were tossing and
turning all night.

821
00:51:31,180 --> 00:51:32,946
No, I-I'm fine.

822
00:51:34,349 --> 00:51:36,550
Well, if you're fine...

823
00:51:38,153 --> 00:51:39,586
...care to,

824
00:51:39,588 --> 00:51:41,488
join me in the shower?

825
00:51:49,765 --> 00:51:52,132
I can't.

826
00:51:52,134 --> 00:51:53,534
- I'm sorry, I got to...
- Go?

827
00:51:53,536 --> 00:51:54,768
Yeah.

828
00:51:56,838 --> 00:51:58,639
Love you.

829
00:52:05,648 --> 00:52:06,914
You got something to say,

830
00:52:06,916 --> 00:52:08,415
why don't you say it
to my face, man?!

831
00:52:08,417 --> 00:52:09,817
Come on.

832
00:52:14,090 --> 00:52:15,322
Bring it!

833
00:52:16,759 --> 00:52:17,958
Fine, he stabs you.

834
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:19,093
One of yours stabs him

835
00:52:19,095 --> 00:52:20,227
and so on and so on

836
00:52:20,229 --> 00:52:21,328
until there's none of you left.

837
00:52:21,330 --> 00:52:22,262
You want vengeance,

838
00:52:22,264 --> 00:52:23,764
you better dig two graves.

839
00:52:23,766 --> 00:52:25,299
One for him and one for you.

840
00:52:25,301 --> 00:52:26,867
Who's gonna dig yours?

841
00:52:33,074 --> 00:52:34,575
I've tried everything I know.

842
00:52:34,577 --> 00:52:37,611
Ben's video isn't on his
phone or on the cloud.

843
00:52:37,613 --> 00:52:39,079
It's like it...

844
00:52:39,081 --> 00:52:40,614
Was never there?

845
00:52:40,616 --> 00:52:42,583
You're not gonna,
like, fire me, right?

846
00:52:42,585 --> 00:52:43,984
I just got a condo.

847
00:52:46,254 --> 00:52:47,821
Those men on the video,

848
00:52:47,823 --> 00:52:49,256
they can't all be the same guy.

849
00:52:49,258 --> 00:52:50,391
That is...

850
00:52:50,393 --> 00:52:52,526
It's crazy.

851
00:52:55,697 --> 00:52:58,565
Ship that off to Billingsley,
all right?

852
00:52:58,567 --> 00:53:01,702
I'm gonna go ahead
and call in a few favors

853
00:53:01,704 --> 00:53:02,770
while we're at...

854
00:53:02,772 --> 00:53:04,872
Excuse...

855
00:53:07,308 --> 00:53:08,642
Junior?

856
00:53:08,644 --> 00:53:11,078
Hey, Barbie.

857
00:53:13,148 --> 00:53:15,048
You're dead.

858
00:53:15,050 --> 00:53:16,483
Not the last time I checked.

859
00:53:16,485 --> 00:53:17,551
Yo!

860
00:53:17,553 --> 00:53:18,752
Incoming.

861
00:53:21,656 --> 00:53:22,856
What are you doing here?

862
00:53:22,858 --> 00:53:25,759
I know, I feel bad that
I missed the memorial,

863
00:53:25,761 --> 00:53:27,027
but my bike broke down.

864
00:53:27,029 --> 00:53:29,062
We haven't seen you since...

865
00:53:29,731 --> 00:53:31,432
Marrakech?

866
00:53:32,767 --> 00:53:34,298
You were building homes

867
00:53:34,322 --> 00:53:36,036
- for the poor.
- Yeah. How weird was it

868
00:53:36,038 --> 00:53:38,238
that we ran into each other
in Africa,

869
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:39,640
of all places?

870
00:53:39,642 --> 00:53:42,637
You still seeing that hottie
that drank us under the table?

871
00:53:42,676 --> 00:53:44,286
- What was her name?
- Eva.

872
00:53:44,317 --> 00:53:46,167
Yeah, she's actually here
with me in Chester's Mill.

873
00:53:46,214 --> 00:53:47,414
Yeah, yeah,
I'd love to see her.

874
00:53:47,416 --> 00:53:49,116
You know,
minus the crap tequila.

875
00:53:50,565 --> 00:53:52,786
Well, I'm not sure how long
we'll be here in town.

876
00:53:52,788 --> 00:53:54,922
No worries.

877
00:53:54,924 --> 00:53:57,124
I know it must be rough for you
being back here.

878
00:53:57,126 --> 00:53:59,393
I think about Julia
all the time.

879
00:53:59,395 --> 00:54:01,595
Yeah, me, too.

880
00:54:02,530 --> 00:54:05,599
Just glad you were able
to move on.

881
00:54:05,601 --> 00:54:07,434
If anyone deserves
happiness, it's you.

882
00:54:07,436 --> 00:54:09,136
I appreciate that.

883
00:54:09,138 --> 00:54:11,138
I'm gonna let you two catch up.

884
00:54:11,140 --> 00:54:12,539
I got to go check on something,

885
00:54:12,541 --> 00:54:13,807
but it's good
seeing you, Junior.

886
00:54:13,809 --> 00:54:15,409
You, too, man.

887
00:54:22,750 --> 00:54:25,486
Do you really think
this will work?

888
00:54:25,488 --> 00:54:28,322
When Barbie used the dome
like this to write me a message,

889
00:54:28,324 --> 00:54:30,290
he was taken away by armed men.

890
00:54:30,292 --> 00:54:32,493
They were watching us.

891
00:54:32,495 --> 00:54:33,794
My father's men?

892
00:54:33,796 --> 00:54:36,296
Let's hope
they're still watching.

893
00:54:38,299 --> 00:54:39,466
She needs the egg.

894
00:54:39,468 --> 00:54:41,468
Let me take the egg
back to Chester's Mill.

895
00:54:41,470 --> 00:54:43,704
I-I think that the dome
may very well

896
00:54:43,706 --> 00:54:45,172
be its power source.

897
00:54:45,174 --> 00:54:46,907
You know, 25 years ago,

898
00:54:46,909 --> 00:54:49,209
a meteor storm bombarded
the Earth.

899
00:54:51,045 --> 00:54:53,447
A year after that,

900
00:54:53,449 --> 00:54:56,183
the first fragments
of one of these so-called eggs

901
00:54:56,185 --> 00:54:59,086
was found in a meteor near
our drilling site in Alaska.

902
00:54:59,088 --> 00:55:00,687
With the government's blessing,

903
00:55:00,689 --> 00:55:03,290
I've devoted the resources
of this company

904
00:55:03,292 --> 00:55:05,759
to track down every meteor
that fell that night.

905
00:55:05,761 --> 00:55:09,162
This was the only egg
that was found intact.

906
00:55:09,164 --> 00:55:10,764
So you can imagine my reluctance

907
00:55:10,766 --> 00:55:13,734
to letting it leave
this facility.

908
00:55:13,736 --> 00:55:16,637
If the egg isn't returned,

909
00:55:16,639 --> 00:55:18,839
we risk losing everyone inside.

910
00:55:18,841 --> 00:55:21,742
I don't give a damn
about anyone in Chester's Mill.

911
00:55:21,744 --> 00:55:23,577
No offense to your daughter.

912
00:55:23,579 --> 00:55:26,313
Your son is trapped
under the dome as well, no?

913
00:55:26,315 --> 00:55:28,215
That's not relevant.

914
00:55:28,217 --> 00:55:30,684
No, no, no, no, I-I disagree.

915
00:55:30,686 --> 00:55:33,053
If I allow you to take this egg
back to Chester's Mill,

916
00:55:33,055 --> 00:55:34,187
it's a one-way ticket.

917
00:55:34,189 --> 00:55:36,590
I need to know
that you're doing this

918
00:55:36,592 --> 00:55:37,891
for the good of the company,

919
00:55:37,893 --> 00:55:40,427
and not
for some sentimental reason.

920
00:55:40,429 --> 00:55:42,729
We want the same thing.

921
00:55:42,731 --> 00:55:46,066
To unlock and harvest
the power of the egg

922
00:55:46,068 --> 00:55:48,669
and the secrets it holds,

923
00:55:48,671 --> 00:55:51,171
regardless of costs.

924
00:55:54,042 --> 00:55:56,243
You think my father
got my message?

925
00:55:56,245 --> 00:55:58,445
I have to believe he did.

926
00:56:00,214 --> 00:56:02,716
And this is where
he'll surface from Zenith.

927
00:56:04,252 --> 00:56:06,520
What was it like
in the cocoons?

928
00:56:08,890 --> 00:56:10,924
Being asleep.

929
00:56:14,095 --> 00:56:15,529
What is it?

930
00:56:16,331 --> 00:56:19,733
If my father returns
with the egg,

931
00:56:19,735 --> 00:56:21,568
what do I even say to him?

932
00:56:21,570 --> 00:56:23,403
It's been so long.

933
00:56:23,405 --> 00:56:26,740
You don't have to say anything.

934
00:56:26,742 --> 00:56:28,275
He's your father.

935
00:56:42,391 --> 00:56:44,024
Are you okay?

936
00:56:45,728 --> 00:56:47,160
Yeah, I would be,

937
00:56:47,162 --> 00:56:48,862
if the world
would stop spinning.

938
00:56:48,864 --> 00:56:51,164
You need to rest,

939
00:56:51,166 --> 00:56:53,233
conserve your strength.

940
00:56:53,235 --> 00:56:55,135
- I can take the first watch.
- No.

941
00:56:55,137 --> 00:56:58,105
No, Julia.

942
00:56:58,107 --> 00:56:59,806
Lay down.

943
00:56:59,808 --> 00:57:02,676
You've always taken
such good care of me.

944
00:57:02,678 --> 00:57:04,745
Always trusted me.

945
00:57:04,747 --> 00:57:07,881
Let me do
this one small thing for you.

946
00:57:07,883 --> 00:57:10,484
I'll wake you at the first sign
of my father.

947
00:57:40,181 --> 00:57:41,481
Eagle one?

948
00:57:41,483 --> 00:57:43,250
How should we proceed?

949
00:57:43,252 --> 00:57:45,919
Just hold off until the team
has arrived.

950
00:57:45,921 --> 00:57:48,155
Also, establish a permanent
comm link

951
00:57:48,157 --> 00:57:50,357
once you're inside the dome.

952
00:58:23,224 --> 00:58:25,625
Melanie?

953
00:58:25,627 --> 00:58:27,294
I can't believe it's really you.

954
00:58:28,096 --> 00:58:29,529
Did you bring it?

955
00:58:29,531 --> 00:58:30,597
Is that the egg?

956
00:58:30,599 --> 00:58:31,965
Of course, sweetheart.

957
00:58:33,468 --> 00:58:35,702
You know I'd do anything
for you.

958
00:58:37,138 --> 00:58:39,406
You're my daughter.

959
00:58:44,278 --> 00:58:45,579
But I'm not.

960
00:59:22,401 --> 00:59:25,068
Dale?

961
00:59:25,070 --> 00:59:26,203
I got your text.

962
00:59:26,205 --> 00:59:27,771
Why are we here?

963
00:59:27,773 --> 00:59:28,772
How did we meet?

964
00:59:28,774 --> 00:59:30,574
Are you serious?

965
00:59:30,576 --> 00:59:31,641
Eva, please,

966
00:59:31,643 --> 00:59:32,709
this is important.

967
00:59:32,711 --> 00:59:33,677
How did we meet?

968
00:59:33,679 --> 00:59:37,347
It was at that dive bar
in Marrakech.

969
00:59:37,349 --> 00:59:39,249
Your tall friend
kept buying me drinks,

970
00:59:39,251 --> 00:59:40,784
but all I could look at was you.

971
00:59:40,786 --> 00:59:42,452
His name?

972
00:59:42,454 --> 00:59:43,687
What was his name?

973
00:59:43,689 --> 00:59:46,323
I think it was James?

974
00:59:46,325 --> 00:59:47,924
But you and Hunter
kept calling him Junior.

975
00:59:47,926 --> 00:59:50,093
Babe, what is this about?

976
00:59:51,896 --> 00:59:53,997
Okay, this is gonna sound crazy,

977
00:59:53,999 --> 00:59:56,132
all right, but I need you
to believe me here.

978
00:59:56,134 --> 00:59:57,367
His name was James Rennie,

979
00:59:57,369 --> 01:00:01,371
and his name was
on this wall yesterday.

980
01:00:01,373 --> 01:00:03,440
That's not possible.

981
01:00:03,442 --> 01:00:06,076
Everything is just jumbled up
in my head.

982
01:00:06,078 --> 01:00:07,177
You and me,

983
01:00:07,179 --> 01:00:08,678
Marrakech, Kabul,

984
01:00:08,680 --> 01:00:10,013
the bed-and-breakfast
in Belgrade.

985
01:00:10,015 --> 01:00:11,081
But now,

986
01:00:11,083 --> 01:00:13,517
I've got all these
other memories, too.

987
01:00:13,519 --> 01:00:16,052
I saw Junior's body, okay?

988
01:00:16,054 --> 01:00:18,989
He died that day
along with his father and Julia

989
01:00:18,991 --> 01:00:20,891
- the day that dome came down.
- Okay.

990
01:00:20,893 --> 01:00:23,159
I'm so sorry.
This is my fault.

991
01:00:23,161 --> 01:00:24,828
I thought coming back
to Chester's Mill

992
01:00:24,830 --> 01:00:27,163
would be good for you, for us,

993
01:00:27,165 --> 01:00:28,365
but I can see now that
it's just upsetting you.

994
01:00:28,367 --> 01:00:29,599
No, you-you,
but you're not listening to me.

995
01:00:29,601 --> 01:00:30,767
It's more than that.

996
01:00:30,769 --> 01:00:32,369
It's the-the-these places,

997
01:00:32,371 --> 01:00:34,271
these people,
something is wrong here.

998
01:00:34,273 --> 01:00:36,373
It's not making sense.

999
01:00:37,742 --> 01:00:39,409
What?

1000
01:00:41,045 --> 01:00:41,878
Dale?

1001
01:00:41,880 --> 01:00:43,046
Hey, you.

1002
01:00:47,151 --> 01:00:48,785
I beg you!

1003
01:00:49,387 --> 01:00:51,555
No, I killed you.

1004
01:00:51,557 --> 01:00:52,722
What are you, watching me?!

1005
01:00:52,724 --> 01:00:53,957
Dale, let him go!

1006
01:00:53,959 --> 01:00:55,058
What are you doing?

1007
01:00:55,060 --> 01:00:56,126
- You don't understand. I...
- No.

1008
01:00:56,128 --> 01:00:58,895
- Don't do this!
- He was in the video, okay?

1009
01:00:58,897 --> 01:01:00,363
That's what Ben
wanted to show me.

1010
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:01,531
Then the video disappeared.

1011
01:01:01,533 --> 01:01:03,066
Ben told me before he died

1012
01:01:03,068 --> 01:01:05,602
that he felt like someone
was watching him, okay?

1013
01:01:05,604 --> 01:01:07,571
That-that all of
this was not real.

1014
01:01:07,573 --> 01:01:09,839
Okay, sweetie,
you're scaring me.

1015
01:01:09,841 --> 01:01:11,308
Just take my hand.

1016
01:01:11,310 --> 01:01:12,976
You've been under
so much stress.

1017
01:01:12,978 --> 01:01:14,811
We can... we can
go back to the motel,

1018
01:01:14,813 --> 01:01:16,780
or we can get
in the car and drive away.

1019
01:01:16,782 --> 01:01:18,515
We never have
to come back here again.

1020
01:01:18,517 --> 01:01:19,749
I-I can't, okay?

1021
01:01:19,751 --> 01:01:22,052
Not until I figure out
what's going on here.

1022
01:01:22,054 --> 01:01:24,421
Dale!

1023
01:01:26,791 --> 01:01:29,826
Focus on your breathing.

1024
01:01:29,828 --> 01:01:32,829
Focus on just being.

1025
01:01:32,831 --> 01:01:36,800
Let your thoughts
flow through you

1026
01:01:36,802 --> 01:01:40,370
until there are none.

1027
01:01:40,372 --> 01:01:41,671
Eyes.

1028
01:01:41,673 --> 01:01:42,906
How do you...?

1029
01:01:42,908 --> 01:01:45,508
Because I'm focused,
and you're not. Again.

1030
01:01:45,510 --> 01:01:47,911
Breathe.

1031
01:01:49,013 --> 01:01:51,348
This is stupid.

1032
01:01:51,350 --> 01:01:54,618
I take it you spoke with Norrie?

1033
01:01:54,620 --> 01:01:56,286
I'm so pissed at her.

1034
01:01:56,288 --> 01:01:58,888
Life becomes so much
easier when you learn

1035
01:01:58,890 --> 01:02:02,092
to accept the apology
you never got.

1036
01:02:02,094 --> 01:02:05,228
You can't expect her
to be sorry for being happy.

1037
01:02:05,230 --> 01:02:10,100
She said I was still trapped
under a dome because of Angie.

1038
01:02:11,168 --> 01:02:12,435
Am I?

1039
01:02:12,437 --> 01:02:14,604
Let me ask you something.

1040
01:02:14,606 --> 01:02:18,141
You have always dreamed
of being an engineer,

1041
01:02:18,143 --> 01:02:20,610
a builder, an inventor,
so, why do you think

1042
01:02:20,612 --> 01:02:23,413
you haven't been able to
send in your acceptance letter

1043
01:02:23,415 --> 01:02:27,017
to Cal Tech, a place
to accomplish all your goals?

1044
01:02:27,019 --> 01:02:30,487
It just... doesn't feel right.

1045
01:02:32,790 --> 01:02:35,191
Joe, I can't tell you
how to feel.

1046
01:02:35,193 --> 01:02:38,428
But... if you really
want to know

1047
01:02:38,430 --> 01:02:40,497
whether you're still living
under a dome,

1048
01:02:40,499 --> 01:02:42,632
maybe it's time you

1049
01:02:42,634 --> 01:02:45,101
forgive the person
who put you there?

1050
01:02:45,103 --> 01:02:46,970
No. No way.

1051
01:02:46,972 --> 01:02:48,705
You have kept your feelings

1052
01:02:48,707 --> 01:02:50,974
regarding Sam buried
for so long,

1053
01:02:50,976 --> 01:02:52,942
they're like a chain
weighing you down.

1054
01:02:52,944 --> 01:02:54,644
I don't want them to stop you

1055
01:02:54,646 --> 01:02:56,446
from reaching your
true potential.

1056
01:02:56,448 --> 01:02:58,848
I have nothing to say
to Sam Verdreaux.

1057
01:02:58,850 --> 01:03:00,550
Then just listen.

1058
01:03:00,552 --> 01:03:02,018
He's as much

1059
01:03:02,020 --> 01:03:03,687
a prisoner of the
past as you are.

1060
01:03:03,689 --> 01:03:04,788
The difference is,

1061
01:03:04,790 --> 01:03:07,924
you're the one holding
all the keys.

1062
01:03:24,709 --> 01:03:26,476
Nice ride.

1063
01:03:26,478 --> 01:03:28,478
Thanks. And you are...?

1064
01:03:28,480 --> 01:03:31,147
Christine. Christine Price.

1065
01:03:31,149 --> 01:03:32,882
Better not.

1066
01:03:32,884 --> 01:03:34,584
I heard you were back in town.

1067
01:03:34,586 --> 01:03:35,852
Who from?

1068
01:03:35,854 --> 01:03:38,054
Your friend Hunter.

1069
01:03:38,056 --> 01:03:40,223
All it takes is a free latte,

1070
01:03:40,225 --> 01:03:42,592
and you'd be amazed
what people tell you.

1071
01:03:42,594 --> 01:03:44,761
You the town shrink?

1072
01:03:44,763 --> 01:03:47,363
Well, I prefer therapist,

1073
01:03:47,365 --> 01:03:50,934
but, yes, I help places
like Chester's Mill heal

1074
01:03:50,936 --> 01:03:52,469
after a natural disaster.

1075
01:03:52,471 --> 01:03:54,337
Yeah, there was nothing natural
about the dome.

1076
01:03:54,339 --> 01:03:59,142
Well, unnatural disaster just
sounds a little too Fox News.

1077
01:04:01,011 --> 01:04:03,346
It's a shame we didn't
get to meet last year.

1078
01:04:03,348 --> 01:04:05,515
By the time I was
assigned to here,

1079
01:04:05,517 --> 01:04:08,017
you were just... gone.

1080
01:04:08,019 --> 01:04:10,320
Nothing to keep me here.

1081
01:04:10,322 --> 01:04:13,156
We missed you
at the memorial yesterday.

1082
01:04:13,158 --> 01:04:16,493
Yeah, I had some trouble
with my bike.

1083
01:04:16,495 --> 01:04:20,597
That's kind of convenient,

1084
01:04:20,599 --> 01:04:22,265
don't you think?

1085
01:04:22,267 --> 01:04:24,167
Showing up the
day after a tribute

1086
01:04:24,169 --> 01:04:25,969
to everyone the town lost,

1087
01:04:25,971 --> 01:04:28,138
including your father?

1088
01:04:28,140 --> 01:04:30,039
Town didn't lose my father.

1089
01:04:30,041 --> 01:04:31,775
I killed him to protect it.

1090
01:04:31,777 --> 01:04:33,109
So if the reason you're here is

1091
01:04:33,111 --> 01:04:35,011
to see how I'm doing
since the dome came down,

1092
01:04:35,013 --> 01:04:38,181
ridding myself of my father was
the best thing I've ever done.

1093
01:04:38,183 --> 01:04:40,683
Now, if you don't mind...

1094
01:04:41,485 --> 01:04:44,187
I'm just curious.

1095
01:04:44,189 --> 01:04:46,489
If ridding yourself

1096
01:04:46,491 --> 01:04:49,092
of your father is the best
thing you've ever done,

1097
01:04:49,094 --> 01:04:52,128
why haven't you sold his house?

1098
01:04:52,130 --> 01:04:54,264
Lady, why do you even care?

1099
01:04:54,266 --> 01:04:58,401
Because like it or not,
James Rennie, you belong here.

1100
01:04:58,403 --> 01:04:59,969
You're part of this town.

1101
01:04:59,971 --> 01:05:01,971
You're part of a community
that needs you right now.

1102
01:05:01,973 --> 01:05:03,573
I can never be part
of this town.

1103
01:05:03,575 --> 01:05:05,008
My father made sure of that.

1104
01:05:05,010 --> 01:05:06,609
You want to know why I left?

1105
01:05:06,611 --> 01:05:09,312
'Cause everyone around here
thinks I'm just like him.

1106
01:05:09,314 --> 01:05:12,849
Then, maybe,
it's time you stop running away

1107
01:05:12,851 --> 01:05:16,019
and show them that you're not.

1108
01:06:33,520 --> 01:06:35,888
Wakey, wakey, sleeping beauty.

1109
01:06:46,066 --> 01:06:48,501
Tell me who the hell that is?

1110
01:06:51,905 --> 01:06:53,606
I <i>asked...</i>

1111
01:06:53,608 --> 01:06:55,708
Don Barbara.

1112
01:06:55,710 --> 01:06:57,677
That's Barbie's old man?

1113
01:06:57,679 --> 01:07:00,212
How'd he get in Chester's Mill?

1114
01:07:00,214 --> 01:07:03,749
Maybe he would've told you
if you hadn't have killed him.

1115
01:07:03,751 --> 01:07:06,485
You think I did this?

1116
01:07:06,487 --> 01:07:09,188
Wouldn't be the first
innocent person you've killed.

1117
01:07:09,190 --> 01:07:11,123
Well, I'll give it to you.

1118
01:07:11,125 --> 01:07:14,327
You got a pair on you,
throwing around accusations,

1119
01:07:14,329 --> 01:07:16,028
considering I'm the one
holding the gun.

1120
01:07:16,030 --> 01:07:17,596
Where is Melanie,
and where's the egg?

1121
01:07:17,598 --> 01:07:18,898
Or did you kill her, too?

1122
01:07:18,900 --> 01:07:21,567
The egg?
I got rid of that damn thing.

1123
01:07:21,569 --> 01:07:23,703
Don was bringing it
back to Chester's Mill.

1124
01:07:23,705 --> 01:07:24,804
What, are you insane?

1125
01:07:24,806 --> 01:07:25,938
After everything
that egg has done,

1126
01:07:25,940 --> 01:07:27,473
you wanted him
to bring it back here?

1127
01:07:27,475 --> 01:07:28,607
That thing is evil.

1128
01:07:28,609 --> 01:07:30,876
No, evil is shooting
your own son.

1129
01:07:30,878 --> 01:07:33,079
- Well, he shot me first.
- Jim,

1130
01:07:33,081 --> 01:07:36,048
everyone in this town is trapped
in the tunnels under the dome,

1131
01:07:36,050 --> 01:07:37,249
including your son.

1132
01:07:37,251 --> 01:07:38,851
Junior's trapped?

1133
01:07:38,853 --> 01:07:41,220
So, if you don't have Melanie,
and you don't have the egg,

1134
01:07:41,222 --> 01:07:42,788
then get out of my way!

1135
01:07:42,790 --> 01:07:46,425
Listen, if you're such
a great reporter, Shumway,

1136
01:07:46,427 --> 01:07:47,593
answer me this.

1137
01:07:47,595 --> 01:07:48,794
Why would I kill this guy,

1138
01:07:48,796 --> 01:07:51,130
then bring you over
to show you the body?

1139
01:07:51,132 --> 01:07:53,099
Face it... you got played.

1140
01:07:53,101 --> 01:07:55,067
Melanie killed that guy,
then left you behind

1141
01:07:55,069 --> 01:07:57,670
so she could take that egg
and do God knows what.

1142
01:07:57,672 --> 01:07:59,872
Melanie would never betray me.
She's not like you.

1143
01:07:59,874 --> 01:08:02,308
Well, that's kind of my point.
She's not like any of us.

1144
01:08:02,310 --> 01:08:03,676
Nobody gets to come back
from the dead.

1145
01:08:03,678 --> 01:08:04,810
You're wrong about her.

1146
01:08:04,812 --> 01:08:06,379
How many people have to suffer

1147
01:08:06,381 --> 01:08:08,914
because you can't see what's
right in front of you?

1148
01:08:08,916 --> 01:08:11,984
That egg, this dome,
that girl...

1149
01:08:11,986 --> 01:08:13,753
they cost me my wife.

1150
01:08:13,755 --> 01:08:15,621
Move!

1151
01:08:15,623 --> 01:08:18,624
You're so high and mighty,
aren't you?

1152
01:08:18,626 --> 01:08:21,460
I'm not the only one in this
town with blood on his hands.

1153
01:08:21,462 --> 01:08:23,195
People are dead because of you.

1154
01:08:23,197 --> 01:08:24,330
Your faith

1155
01:08:24,332 --> 01:08:28,467
in this dome has made you
blind, deaf and dumb.

1156
01:08:29,637 --> 01:08:32,004
That is the second time
you have called me dumb,

1157
01:08:32,006 --> 01:08:33,839
and I wouldn't do it again.

1158
01:08:33,841 --> 01:08:35,708
Now, if you're gonna
shoot me, do it.

1159
01:08:35,710 --> 01:08:37,109
Otherwise, I'm leaving now.

1160
01:08:37,111 --> 01:08:39,378
My, my, the monarch's
got a temper.

1161
01:08:39,380 --> 01:08:41,580
Go to hell.

1162
01:08:43,617 --> 01:08:46,052
Truth hurts, doesn't it?

1163
01:09:21,755 --> 01:09:23,622
Yeah, there's a
space right here.

1164
01:09:23,624 --> 01:09:25,291
Yeah, room seven, I believe.

1165
01:09:25,293 --> 01:09:26,659
Yeah...

1166
01:09:26,661 --> 01:09:29,261
Honey, just tell housekeeping.

1167
01:09:29,263 --> 01:09:31,197
This is our room
right here, so, yeah,

1168
01:09:31,199 --> 01:09:35,301
we could just,
bring it in over here.

1169
01:09:35,303 --> 01:09:37,303
Maggie, I just got
to get the last bag...

1170
01:09:37,305 --> 01:09:39,371
You have your I.D.?

1171
01:10:09,302 --> 01:10:11,804
Yup.

1172
01:10:11,806 --> 01:10:13,772
Dale?

1173
01:10:14,608 --> 01:10:16,475
Who is this?

1174
01:10:16,477 --> 01:10:18,577
It's Christine Price.
We met at the memorial.

1175
01:10:18,579 --> 01:10:20,179
I'm with Eva at the hospital.

1176
01:10:20,181 --> 01:10:21,380
I think

1177
01:10:21,382 --> 01:10:23,149
that you should get here
right away.

1178
01:10:34,996 --> 01:10:36,581
How's Eva?
What happened?

1179
01:10:36,613 --> 01:10:38,364
She called me, wanted to
meet at the Sweetbriar.

1180
01:10:38,366 --> 01:10:39,765
She was upset about your fight.

1181
01:10:39,767 --> 01:10:42,234
We were waiting for our food
when she doubled over in pain.

1182
01:10:42,236 --> 01:10:43,502
I helped her to the bathroom,

1183
01:10:43,504 --> 01:10:45,137
and that's when she
noticed she was bleeding.

1184
01:10:45,139 --> 01:10:46,772
- She was bleeding? What...?
- Oh, no, no.

1185
01:10:46,774 --> 01:10:48,507
The doctor's with her now.
He said that Eva

1186
01:10:48,509 --> 01:10:50,943
and the baby are
gonna be just fine.

1187
01:10:54,548 --> 01:10:56,715
The baby?

1188
01:11:42,518 --> 01:11:44,285
What the hell?

1189
01:11:45,253 --> 01:11:46,420
Get.

1190
01:11:48,890 --> 01:11:50,291
Get!

1191
01:11:52,561 --> 01:11:54,528
Get!

1192
01:11:54,530 --> 01:11:56,864
Go on, get out of here!

1193
01:12:02,304 --> 01:12:04,271
Stupid mutt.

1194
01:12:31,601 --> 01:12:34,402
So why do they call it
<i>Hard</i> Lemonade?

1195
01:12:34,404 --> 01:12:36,804
Because...

1196
01:12:36,806 --> 01:12:39,306
I got nothing.

1197
01:12:39,308 --> 01:12:40,941
Well, do you like beer?

1198
01:12:40,943 --> 01:12:43,210
I hate beer.

1199
01:12:43,212 --> 01:12:45,379
To hating beer.

1200
01:12:56,158 --> 01:12:57,625
Was Joe right?

1201
01:12:57,627 --> 01:12:59,751
Have I become

1202
01:12:59,782 --> 01:13:03,597
that awful, stuck-up college bitch
that everyone hates?

1203
01:13:03,599 --> 01:13:07,735
And we were doing so well
without talking about Joe.

1204
01:13:07,737 --> 01:13:10,571
Is that what this is all about?

1205
01:13:12,541 --> 01:13:14,308
Screw him.

1206
01:13:14,310 --> 01:13:17,111
I like being in a sorority.

1207
01:13:17,113 --> 01:13:19,346
I love, for the first
time in my life,

1208
01:13:19,348 --> 01:13:21,382
not being so angry all the time

1209
01:13:21,384 --> 01:13:23,184
because I never fit in.

1210
01:13:23,186 --> 01:13:24,685
I totally get that.

1211
01:13:24,687 --> 01:13:27,955
I feel the same thing
working for Barbie.

1212
01:13:27,957 --> 01:13:32,259
I was always this loner out to
get back at the system, but now...

1213
01:13:32,261 --> 01:13:34,829
I-I don't know, you know,
I feel like...

1214
01:13:34,831 --> 01:13:37,431
I have...
direction and purpose,

1215
01:13:37,433 --> 01:13:40,701
that there's more to my life
than just looking out for myself.

1216
01:13:40,703 --> 01:13:43,370
I never want to go back
to being that guy.

1217
01:13:44,206 --> 01:13:45,606
The way I see it,

1218
01:13:45,608 --> 01:13:47,942
you can do what Joe
wants you to do,

1219
01:13:47,944 --> 01:13:49,744
or you can just...

1220
01:13:49,746 --> 01:13:51,378
move forward,

1221
01:13:51,380 --> 01:13:53,447
allow yourself to be happy.

1222
01:13:53,449 --> 01:13:55,249
Just make sure it's your choice,

1223
01:13:55,251 --> 01:13:57,785
what it is that you want.

1224
01:14:18,206 --> 01:14:20,040
Hey, you.

1225
01:14:20,042 --> 01:14:21,709
How long have you been here?

1226
01:14:21,711 --> 01:14:23,577
About an hour or so.

1227
01:14:26,516 --> 01:14:29,216
Why didn't you tell me
about the baby?

1228
01:14:30,051 --> 01:14:32,253
I wanted to.

1229
01:14:33,622 --> 01:14:37,091
I just thought it would be
better after the memorial,

1230
01:14:37,093 --> 01:14:39,026
so that you wouldn't
feel trapped.

1231
01:14:39,028 --> 01:14:40,494
Trapped?

1232
01:14:40,496 --> 01:14:42,229
Why would you even think that?

1233
01:14:42,231 --> 01:14:44,231
Dale...

1234
01:14:44,233 --> 01:14:47,234
I jumped into this relationship
with both feet.

1235
01:14:47,236 --> 01:14:49,503
You seem to have one foot
in the past with Julia

1236
01:14:49,505 --> 01:14:51,572
and the other foot
in the future with me, and...

1237
01:14:51,574 --> 01:14:53,574
I want to be with you.

1238
01:14:53,576 --> 01:14:55,676
I want to have this baby.

1239
01:15:02,618 --> 01:15:05,586
What I feel for you...

1240
01:15:05,588 --> 01:15:07,421
is real.

1241
01:15:07,423 --> 01:15:09,723
And this baby is real.

1242
01:15:09,725 --> 01:15:12,226
I know what I want.

1243
01:15:13,328 --> 01:15:15,396
But do you?

1244
01:15:23,305 --> 01:15:26,140
I'll be over here
if you need anything.

1245
01:15:26,142 --> 01:15:27,942
Okay.

1246
01:15:31,012 --> 01:15:32,546
Sit.

1247
01:15:38,153 --> 01:15:42,723
Look, Joe, I know this must be
damn near impossible for you.

1248
01:15:42,725 --> 01:15:47,528
I don't want you to think
that I've asked you here to...

1249
01:15:47,530 --> 01:15:49,296
explain what I did,

1250
01:15:49,298 --> 01:15:52,700
or that somehow I'm not
responsible for my actions.

1251
01:15:53,535 --> 01:15:55,703
So why am I here?

1252
01:15:57,306 --> 01:16:01,208
Because as part of my sentence,
I've been...

1253
01:16:01,210 --> 01:16:03,544
working with other prisoners.

1254
01:16:03,546 --> 01:16:05,379
Trying to help them move on

1255
01:16:05,381 --> 01:16:07,615
and get their lives
back on track.

1256
01:16:07,617 --> 01:16:12,119
I guess, in a way, it's also...

1257
01:16:12,121 --> 01:16:15,990
forced me to take
a long look at myself.

1258
01:16:17,292 --> 01:16:19,293
My drinking.

1259
01:16:20,161 --> 01:16:21,829
My shame.

1260
01:16:21,831 --> 01:16:23,631
The reason I wanted to see you

1261
01:16:23,633 --> 01:16:26,066
is because I wanted
to look you in the eyes

1262
01:16:26,068 --> 01:16:29,136
and tell you how profoundly
sorry I am for what I did.

1263
01:16:29,138 --> 01:16:31,972
And that I'm doing
everything I can

1264
01:16:31,974 --> 01:16:34,675
to be a different person.

1265
01:16:34,677 --> 01:16:36,310
To be a better person.

1266
01:16:36,312 --> 01:16:38,379
To earn...

1267
01:16:38,381 --> 01:16:40,915
your forgiveness.

1268
01:16:43,318 --> 01:16:45,352
Her name's Angie.

1269
01:16:45,354 --> 01:16:47,321
You haven't said her name once.

1270
01:16:47,323 --> 01:16:49,823
It's Angie.
And you killed her.

1271
01:16:49,825 --> 01:16:52,559
- Joe, I-I...
- No. You don't get to speak.

1272
01:16:52,561 --> 01:16:53,761
It's my turn.

1273
01:16:53,763 --> 01:16:55,429
I didn't come here for you,

1274
01:16:55,431 --> 01:16:57,498
or to hear about how
you're getting on with your life...

1275
01:16:57,500 --> 01:16:58,732
I came for my sister.

1276
01:16:58,734 --> 01:17:00,434
The one person
who meant everything to me

1277
01:17:00,436 --> 01:17:02,202
and who will never get
to move on.

1278
01:17:02,204 --> 01:17:04,972
So if you're done patting
yourself on the back

1279
01:17:04,974 --> 01:17:06,840
for becoming a better person,

1280
01:17:06,842 --> 01:17:09,576
then I want you to know that the
only way I'll ever forgive you

1281
01:17:09,578 --> 01:17:11,979
is when you've suffered the way
that you made Angie suffer.

1282
01:17:36,304 --> 01:17:37,671
Oh, God!

1283
01:17:37,673 --> 01:17:41,141
Hey! Get down!

1284
01:17:41,143 --> 01:17:44,144
Everybody, lock it up now!
Lock it up! Down!

1285
01:18:20,715 --> 01:18:22,683
Melanie.

1286
01:18:22,685 --> 01:18:24,585
What are you doing?

1287
01:18:24,587 --> 01:18:26,520
I couldn't wait for you, Julia.

1288
01:18:26,522 --> 01:18:29,123
Why couldn't you wait for me?

1289
01:18:48,676 --> 01:18:50,677
What's happening?

1290
01:18:50,679 --> 01:18:53,714
Who's in that cocoon, Melanie?

1291
01:18:53,716 --> 01:18:55,716
You'll see.

1292
01:18:55,718 --> 01:18:57,484
You have faith in me,

1293
01:18:57,486 --> 01:18:59,720
- don't you, Julia?
- All I have ever wanted

1294
01:18:59,722 --> 01:19:02,756
is to believe that the dome
is here for a reason.

1295
01:19:02,758 --> 01:19:04,725
But I can't keep
ignoring the truth,

1296
01:19:04,727 --> 01:19:07,361
not when it's staring
me right in the eyes.

1297
01:19:07,363 --> 01:19:09,663
If the cocoon protects
who's inside,

1298
01:19:09,665 --> 01:19:11,865
and Junior freed you...

1299
01:19:11,867 --> 01:19:15,169
how did he cut your cocoon
open when I have the knife?

1300
01:19:30,218 --> 01:19:32,453
What the hell?

1301
01:19:40,795 --> 01:19:43,130
My God.

1302
01:19:46,634 --> 01:19:49,703
Is this what you want, Norrie?

1303
01:19:49,705 --> 01:19:52,139
I'm so, so sorry, Joe.

1304
01:19:56,111 --> 01:19:58,445
Do you love me?

1305
01:20:08,324 --> 01:20:09,823
I'm sorry, Julia.

1306
01:20:09,825 --> 01:20:11,492
A process has begun,

1307
01:20:11,494 --> 01:20:13,160
and I cannot let you interfere.

1308
01:20:13,162 --> 01:20:14,862
I believed in you.

1309
01:20:14,864 --> 01:20:16,830
Don't worry, we'll fix you, too.

1310
01:20:16,832 --> 01:20:18,799
And what about me?

1311
01:20:18,801 --> 01:20:19,967
'Cause I don't know

1312
01:20:19,969 --> 01:20:21,668
who this "we" is...

1313
01:20:21,670 --> 01:20:24,705
but I'll be damned
if I'll let it kill my son.

1314
01:20:25,540 --> 01:20:27,074
No, no, you can't.

1315
01:20:27,076 --> 01:20:29,776
You'll destroy everything!

1316
01:20:29,778 --> 01:20:32,179
What do you say, Red?

1317
01:20:33,616 --> 01:20:35,215
Do it.

1318
01:21:57,832 --> 01:22:00,300
Barbie! It's okay.

1319
01:22:00,302 --> 01:22:03,403
It's me, Julia.

1320
01:22:03,405 --> 01:22:05,272
It's okay now.

1321
01:22:09,210 --> 01:22:12,079
You're safe.

